language=id|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n\n====21 March====\n*[[Indonesian Air Force]] is to fly its [[Lockheed C-130 Hercules|C-130 Hercules]] (A-1333) to the Chinese city of [[Shanghai]] on Saturday to pick up approximately 9 tonnes of medical equipment. The route is [[Malang]]-[[Natuna Regency|Natuna]]-Hainan-Shanghai. The equipment includes disposable masks, [[N-95 masks]], protective clothing, goggles, gloves, shoe covers, infrared thermometers, and surgical caps.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4948247/tni-kerahkan-hercules-angkut-alat-kesehatan-corona-dari-shanghai|title=TNI Kerahkan Hercules Angkut Alat Kesehatan Corona dari Shanghai|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/20/covid-19-indonesian-military-to-get-medical-equipment-from-china.html|title=COVID-19: Indonesian military to get medical equipment from China|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n* One person died after having a fever and headaches. The victim, a Russian citizen, died in his boarding house on Jalan Bukit Tunggal Gang 5, West Denpasar.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.balipost.com/news/2020/03/21/111174/Sempat-Demam,Warga-Rusia-Ditemukan...html|title=Sempat Demam, Warga Rusia Ditemukan Meninggal|last=POST|first=BALI|date=March 21, 2020|publisher=[[Bali Post Media Group]]|website=BALI POST PORTAL BERITA|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* Indonesia announced 81 new cases, totalling 450 cases of COVID-19 infection. Indonesia also announced 20 recovered and 38 deaths, an increase of 6 deaths since 20 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4948271/data-terbaru-kasus-positif-corona-jadi-450-bertambah-81|title=Data Terbaru: Kasus Positif Corona Jadi 450, Bertambah 81|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n====22 March====\n* [[:id:Ikatan Dokter Indonesia|Indonesia Medical Association]] (IDI) announced 6 doctors (dr Toni Daniel Silitonga; dr Ucok Martin SpP; dr Djoko Judodjoko, SpB; dr Hadio Ali SpS; dr Laurentius P, SpKJ; dr Adi Mirsaputra SpTHT) have contracted COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4949139/6-dokter-indonesia-jadi-korban-pandemi-corona-ini-daftarnya|title=6 Dokter Indonesia Jadi Korban Pandemi Corona, Ini Daftarnya|last=Mahardhika|first=Anjar|website=detikHealth|language=id|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n* Indonesia announced 64 new cases, a total of 514 cases. Indonesia also announced 29 recovered and 48 deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4949042/pernyataan-lengkap-pemerintah-soal-514-kasus-corona-per-22-maret|title=Pernyataan Lengkap Pemerintah soal 514 Kasus Corona Per 22 Maret|last=Permana|first=Rakhmad Hidayatulloh|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> An increase of 10 deaths with a death rate of 9.33%, which was the biggest death rate so far.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4949055/pasien-corona-meninggal-48-orang-tingkat-kematian-jadi-93|title=Pasien Corona Meninggal 48 Orang, Tingkat Kematian Jadi 9,3%|last=Permana|first=Rakhmad Hidayatulloh|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n====23 March====\n* Indonesia announced 65 new cases, bringing the total to 579 cases. Indonesia also announced 30 recovered and 49 deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4950124/per-23-maret-kasus-positif-corona-di-indonesia-jadi-579|title=Per 23 Maret, Kasus Positif Corona di Indonesia Jadi 579|last=Ibrahim|first=Gibran Maulana|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n*President Joko Widodo inaugurated the first COVID-19 emergency hospital in the country at the [[Kemayoran Athletes Village|former athlete's village for the 2018 Asian Games]] in [[Kemayoran]], Jakarta. It was slated to be fitted with 3000 beds for patients requiring isolation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/23/09435921/presiden-jokowi-resmikan-rs-darurat-corona-di-wisma-atlet-kemayoran|title=Presiden Jokowi Resmikan RS Darurat Corona di Wisma Atlet Kemayoran|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4949291/dipermak-jadi-rs-hari-ini-wisma-atlet-siap-diisi-pasien-corona|title=Dipermak Jadi RS, Hari Ini Wisma Atlet Siap Diisi Pasien Corona|last=Hamdani|first=Trio|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> Later reports suggested that it would house only 1,800 beds for the first phase.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/as-testing-expands-patients-at-indonesias-athletes-village-turn-hospital-expected-to|title=As coronavirus testing expands, cases at Indonesia's athlete's village-turned-hospital expected to rise dramatically|last=hermesauto|date=2020-03-25|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n\n====24 March====\n* President Joko Widodo announced the cancellation of the annual national examination (''[[National Exam (Indonesia)|Ujian Nasional]]'') for all education levels, except Vocational High School (''Sekolah Menengah Kejuruan, SMK'') that has been done in almost half of all schools in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4951217/jokowi-putuskan-tiadakan-un-2020-imbas-corona|title=Jokowi Putuskan Tiadakan UN 2020 Imbas Corona|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tirto.id/murid-smk-sudah-telanjur-un-nadiem-maaf-kalau-kalian-kecewa-eHlA|title=Murid SMK Sudah Telanjur UN, Nadiem: Maaf Kalau Kalian Kecewa|last=Friana|first=Hendra|website=tirto.id|language=id|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4951361/un-2020-batal-untuk-sma-sudah-kelar-47-untuk-smk|title=UN 2020 Batal untuk SMA, Sudah Kelar 47% untuk SMK|last=Damarjati|first=Danu|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> He also announced measures to ease motorcycle loans for one year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4951070/jokowi-tukang-ojek-jangan-khawatir-cicilan-motor-dilonggarkan-1-tahun|title=Jokowi: Tukang Ojek Jangan Khawatir, Cicilan Motor Dilonggarkan 1 Tahun|last=Erwanti|first=Marlinda Oktavia|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-24}}</ref>\n* Indonesia confirmed 107 more cases, 686 in total.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200324154310-4-147291/bertambah-107-total-positif-corona-di-ri-686-kasus|title=Bertambah 107, Total Positif Corona di RI 686 Kasus|last=Sandi|first=Ferry|date=|website=CNBC Indonesia|language=id-ID|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n====25 March====\n* The [[Ministry of Transportation (Indonesia)|Indonesian Ministry of Transportation]] discouraged everyone from travelling home for the [[Eid al-Fitr]] holiday to contain the spread of the virus.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sugianto |first1=Danang |title=Kemenhub Minta Masyarakat Tidak Mudik, Lebaran Bisa Video Call |url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4952578/kemenhub-minta-masyarakat-tidak-mudik-lebaran-bisa-video-call?tag_from=wp_beritautama&_ga=2.107555403.834036946.1583960210-317182638.1583477810 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |publisher=detik.com |language=id-ID|date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n* Indonesia confirmed 105 more cases and corrected the data from the previous day. It should have said 685, while the previous day's data recorded 686. One patient's name was mistakenly registered in two hospitals. The total number of cases becomes 790.\n\n====26 March====\n* Indonesia announced 103 new cases, bringing the total number to 893.\n* Researchers have estimated that there could be tens of thousands of hidden infections across the country.<ref name=\"FirdausRatcliffe\">{{Cite news|last=Firdaus|first=Febriana|last2=Ratcliffe|first2=Rebecca|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2020/mar/26/indonesia-could-have-thousands-of-hidden-coronavirus-cases-study-says|title=Indonesia's hidden coronavirus cases threaten to overwhelm hospitals|date=2020-03-26|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-27|url-status=live|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n*40 tonnes of medical equipment from China transported to Jakarta.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kumparan.com/kumparannews/40-ton-bantuan-alkes-dari-china-diangkut-garuda-tiba-di-jakarta-malam-ini-1t6Jh6wihWO|title=40 Ton Bantuan Alkes dari China Diangkut Garuda, Tiba di Jakarta Malam Ini|website=kumparan|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n\n====27 March====\n* Indonesia confirmed 153 new positive cases, 1,046 in total. They also announced 9 deaths and 11 recoveries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kompas.com/tren/read/2020/03/27/193000465/update--rincian-kasus-virus-corona-di-28-provinsi-di-indonesia-dan-upaya|title=Update: Rincian Kasus Virus Corona di 28 Provinsi di Indonesia dan Upaya Pemerintah|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*[[Beringharjo]] and Tanah Abang (10 days) markets are closed to prevent COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/ekonomi/20200327161431-92-487587/cegah-corona-pasar-batik-beringharjo-yogyakarta-tutup|title=Cegah Corona, Pasar Batik Beringharjo Yogyakarta Tutup|website=ekonomi|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/27/safety-above-all-tanah-abang-market-closes-for-10-days-faces-ramadan-losses-amid-covid-19.html|title=Safety above all: Tanah Abang market closes for 10 days, faces Ramadan losses amid COVID-19|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*[[Coordinating Ministry for Political, Legal, and Security Affairs (Indonesia)|Coordinating Minister for Political, Legal, and Security Affairs of Indonesia]] [[Mahfud MD]] said that a special law about local lockdown is currently in the works.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Arkyasa |first1=Mahinda |title=Mahfud MD: Govt' Prepares Regulation on Local Quarantine |url=https://en.tempo.co/read/1324774/mahfud-md-govt-prepares-regulation-on-local-quarantine |accessdate=28 March 2020 |publisher=Tempo |date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n====28 March====\n* Indonesia announced 109 more cases, bringing the total number to 1,155.\n* A number of cities decided to issue local lockdowns, such as [[Tegal (city)|the city of Tegal]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Suherdjoko |title=Tegal blocks roads into city in first attempt to impose lockdown in Indonesia |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/26/tegal-blocks-roads-into-city-in-first-attempt-to-impose-lockdown-in-indonesia.html |accessdate=29 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=26 March 2020}}</ref> in Central Java and the province of Papua.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mawel |first1=Benny |title=Papua restricts entry as concerns mount over lack of facilities to treat COVID-19 |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/25/papua-restricts-entry-as-concerns-mount-over-lack-of-facilities-to-treat-covid-19.html |accessdate=29 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Indonesia AirAsia]] suspends all flights from 1 April until at least 21 April for domestic flights and 17 May for international flights.<ref>{{cite news |title=AirAsia Indonesia suspends all flights starting April 1 |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/travel/2020/03/28/airasia-indonesia-suspends-all-flights-starting-april-1.html |accessdate=30 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n====29 March====\n* Indonesia confirmed another 130 new cases, 1,285 in total.\n* The state railway company [[Kereta Api Indonesia]] cancels 28 routes from Jakarta for the month of April.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ramadhian |first1=Nabilla |title=28 Kereta Api Jarak Jauh dari Gambir, Pasar Senen, dan Jakarta Kota Dibatalkan |url=https://travel.kompas.com/read/2020/03/29/112741327/28-kereta-api-jarak-jauh-dari-gambir-pasar-senen-dan-jakarta-kota-dibatalkan |accessdate=30 March 2020 |agency=Kompas |publisher=Kompas}}</ref>\n\n====30 March====\n* Indonesia confirmed 129 new cases, bringing the total number to 1,414.\n*Jokowi orders large-scale social restrictions coupled with 'civil emergency' policies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/30/jokowi-orders-large-scale-social-restrictions-coupled-with-civil-emergency-policies.html|title=Jokowi orders large-scale social restrictions coupled with 'civil emergency' policies|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n====31 March====\n* Indonesia confirmed 114 new cases, 1,528 in total.\n* 30,000 prisoners are planned to be released early to curb spread of COVID-19 inside jails. <ref>{{cite news |last1=Widianto |first1=Stanley |title=Indonesia to release 30,000 prisoners early amid virus concerns |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/indonesia-to-release-30000-prisoners-early-amid-virus-concerns.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n* President [[Joko Widodo]] declared public health emergency and invoked the police to enforce large-scale social distancing policy <ref>{{cite news |title=Jokowi declares COVID-19 health emergency, imposes large-scale social restrictions |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/jokowi-declares-covid-19-health-emergency-imposes-large-scale-social-restrictions.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>, in addition to allocating Rp405 trillion for eradication of COVID-19 and cushioning of social and economical effects due to the pandemic, and announced stimulus for the low-middle class society. <ref>{{cite news |last1=Gorbiano |first1=Marchio Irfan |title=Indonesia announces Rp 405 trillion COVID-19 budget, anticipates 5% deficit in historic move |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/indonesia-announces-rp-405-trillion-covid-19-budget-anticipates-5-deficit-in-historic-move.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=31 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Harsono |first1=Norman |title=Jokowi announces free electricity, discounts for households hardest hit by COVID-19 impacts |url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/jokowi-announces-free-electricity-discounts-for-households-hardest-hit-by-covid-19-impacts.html |accessdate=31 March 2020 |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== April ===\n\n==== 1 April ====\n\n* Indonesia confirmed 149 new cases, bringing the total number to 1,677.\n*300 police students at [[:id:Sekolah_Pembentukan_Perwira|Sekolah Pembentukan Perwira]] (Setukpa) [[:id:Lembaga_Pendidikan_dan_Pelatihan_Kepolisian_Negara_Republik_Indonesia|Lembaga Pendidikan Polri]] (Lemdikpol) in [[Sukabumi]] are quarantined for 14 days after positive rapid test results.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/04/01/18562421/300-polisi-yang-rapid-test-nya-positif-dikarantina-14-hari|title=300 Polisi yang \"Rapid Test\"-nya Positif Dikarantina 14 Hari|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ayobandung.com/read/2020/04/01/84615/positif-corona-300-polisi-setukpa-lemdikpol-di-sukabumi-diisolasi|title=Positif Corona, 300 Polisi Setukpa Lemdikpol di Sukabumi Diisolasi|last=Network|first=Ayo Media|date=2020-04-01|website=AyoBandung.com|language=id|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n====2 April====\n* Indonesia confirmed 113 new cases, bringing the total to 1,790.\n* Indonesia has now banned foreigners from entering its border. Its citizens returning from abroad have to provide health report and do compulsory self-quarantine.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://jakartaglobe.id/news/indonesia-imposes-entry-ban-on-foreigners-makes-quarantine-compulsory-for-returning-citizens\n|title=Indonesia Banned Foreigners From Entering Its Border\n|author=Lenny Tristia Tambun\n|work=Jakarta Globe\n|date=31 March 2020\n|accessdate=3 April 2020\n}}</ref>\n\n====3 April====\n* Indonesia confirmed 196 new cases, the most in a single day since the pandemic began in Indonesia. The total number now is 1,986.\n\n== Cases ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Indonesia medical cases}}\n\n=== Definition ===\nThe [[Ministry of Health (Indonesia)|Ministry of Health of the Republic of Indonesia]] classifies suspects of COVID-19 cases into two levels.<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kemkes.go.id/article/view/20030400004/ini-perbedaan-orang-dalam-pemantauan-dan-pasien-dalam-pengawasan.html|title=Ini Perbedaan Orang dalam Pemantauan dan Pasien dalam Pengawasan|last=|first=|date=3 March 2020|website=Kementerian Kesehatan|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319133557/https://www.kemkes.go.id/article/view/20030400004/ini-perbedaan-orang-dalam-pemantauan-dan-pasien-dalam-pengawasan.html|archive-date=2020-03-19|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n* '''Person Under Monitoring (PUM)''' or ''Orang Dalam Pemantauan (ODP)'' \u2013 is a person who does not show symptoms or has fever and/or coughing or flu, and has traveled from other countries or regions in Indonesia that are believed to have COVID-19 human transmission or has been in contact with a PUS or a positive COVID-19 case. A PUM may be allowed a stay-at-home quarantine for 14 days with constant inspection.\n* '''Patient Under Supervision (PUS)''' or ''Pasien Dalam Pengawasan (PDP)'' \u2013 is a sick PUM showing symptoms of mild to severe pneumonia or who is positive after a rapid test. He or she may be treated at a hospital.\n\nA PUS is then categorized as a positive COVID-19 case if a swab or PCR (polymerase chain reaction) test produce positive results.<ref name=\":13\" /> Due to lower accuracy and fear of false positives, a positive rapid test is not counted into the official number of cases.\n\nOn the other hand, the provincial government of [[Jakarta]] and a few other provinces define PUM and PUS as follows.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://corona.jakarta.go.id/data|title=Jakarta Tanggap COVID-19|last=|first=|date=|website=Jakarta Tanggap COVID-19|language=id|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319133821/https://corona.jakarta.go.id/data|archive-date=2020-03-19|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n* '''PUM''' is a person who shows symptoms of fever (>{{Convert|38|C|F}}) or has a history of fever or [[Acute Respiratory Infection|ARI]] without pneumonia and has a history of travel to an infected country or another region in Indonesia or contact with a positive COVID-19 case in the last 14 days.\n* '''PUS''' is a person who shows symptoms of fever (>{{Convert|38|C|F}}) or has a history of fever, ARI, and mild to severe pneumonia, and has a history of travel to an infected country or another region in Indonesia or contact with a positive COVID-19 case in the last 14 days.\n\n=== Suspected cases ===\nSeveral travellers who had visited or transited through [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bali]] later tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 shortly after their return to [[2019\u201320 coronavirus outbreak in mainland China|China]],<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-indonesia/indonesia-traces-movements-of-chinese-tourist-with-coronavirus-idUSKBN2070YC\n|title=Indonesia traces movements of Chinese tourist with coronavirus\n|author1=Stanley Widianto\n|author2=Agustinus Beo Da Costa\n|author3=Jessica Damiana\n|work=Reuters\n|date=2020-02-13\n|accessdate=2020-03-07\n|language=en\n}}</ref> [[2020 coronavirus outbreak in Japan|Japan]],<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://coconuts.co/bali/news/indonesian-official-says-japanese-coronavirus-patient-who-visited-bali-infected-with-sars-cov-2-not-covid-19/\n|title=Indonesian Official Says Japanese Coronavirus Patient Who Visited Bali Infected With SARS-CoV-2, Not COVID-19\n|work=Coconuts Media\n|date=24 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020\n}}</ref> [[2019\u201320 coronavirus outbreak by country and territory#New Zealand|New Zealand]],<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4919595/terbang-via-bali-wn-selandia-baru-positif-covid-19\n|title=Terbang Via Bali, WN Selandia Baru Positif Covid-19\n|author=Khadijah Nur Azizah\n|work=Detik.com\n|date=29 February 2020|language=id\n|accessdate=2 March 2020\n}}</ref> and [[2020 coronavirus outbreak in Singapore|Singapore]].<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/02/breaking-three-people-in-singaporelatest-to-test-positive-for-covid-19-after-visiting-indonesia.html\n|title=Three people in Singapore latest to test positive for COVID-19 after visiting Indonesia\n|work=The Jakarta Post\n|date=2 March 2020\n|accessdate=2 March 2020\n}}</ref>\n\nAn additional 50 to 70 people were put under surveillance after coming into contact with the first two confirmed COVID-19 patients. This number includes those who had visited Rumah Sakit Mitra Keluarga [[Depok]], the hospital the two confirmed patients were previously admitted to before being transferred to North Jakarta.<ref>{{cite news \n|last1=Siret \n|first1=Mal \n|last2=Jackson \n|first2=Patrick \n|title=EU raises virus risk level as deaths worldwide top 3,000 \n|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/live/world-asia-51701043 \n|accessdate=March 2, 2020 \n|work=BBC News \n|agency=BBC \n|issue=Coronavirus \n|publisher=BBC News \n|date=March 2, 2020 \n|language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{cite news \n|last1=Putra \n|first1=Nanda Perdana \n|title=Wali Kota Depok: 50 Orang Lebih Terindikasi Virus Corona (in Indonesian) \n|url=https://www.liputan6.com/news/read/4191913/wali-kota-depok-50-orang-lebih-terindikasi-virus-corona \n|accessdate=March 2, 2020 \n|work=liputan6.com \n|agency=Liputan 6 \n|issue=Coronavirus \n|publisher=Liputan 6 (local source) \n|date=2 March 2020 \n|language=id}}</ref>\n\nA 37-year-old man who died in a hospital in [[Semarang]] suspected of having COVID-19 reportedly tested negative, and was instead afflicted by [[Influenza A virus subtype H1N1|swine flu]], probably picked up from recent travels to [[2009 flu pandemic in Spain|Spain]].<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://jakartaglobe.id/news/indonesia-says-suspected-coronavirus-patient-dies-of-swine-flu\n|title=Indonesia Says Suspected Coronavirus Patient Dies of Swine Flu\n|work=Jakarta Globe\n|date=27 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020\n}}</ref>\n\nSimilarly, in West Sumatra, two people who returned from a foreign country died at Padang's Hospital (Indonesia: Rumah Sakit Umum Pusat Dr. M. Djamil). On 13 March, a woman who was being treated as a suspect to have contracted COVID-19 after returning from [[Umrah]] has died in [[Padang]]'s hospital.<ref name=\"suspectpadang\">{{Cite web | url=https://regional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/13/18363681/satu-pasien-suspect-corona-meninggal-dunia-di-rsup-m-djamil-padang |title = Satu Pasien Suspect Corona Meninggal Dunia di RSUP M Djamil Padang}}</ref> On 16 March, a 47-year-old man from Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia landed at [[Minangkabau International Airport]] with a fever and showing symptoms of COVID-19.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200316134321-20-483830/sesak-napas-penumpang-airasia-dibawa-ke-rsup-m-djamil-padang | title=Sesak Napas, Penumpang AirAsia Dibawa ke RSUP M Djamil Padang}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://kompas.id/baca/nusantara/2020/03/16/satu-penumpang-dari-malaysia-dirujuk-ke-rsup-dr-m-djamil-padang/ | title=Satu Penumpang dari Malaysia Dirujuk ke RSUP Dr M Djamil Padang| date=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"suspectpadang2\">{{Cite web | url=https://www.antaranews.com/berita/1360154/rsup-m-djamil-padang-masih-periksa-penumpang-pesawat-asal-malaysia | title=RSUP M Djamil Padang masih periksa penumpang pesawat asal Malaysia| date=16 March 2020}}</ref> He was subsequently hospitalized at Padang's hospital and then died on the same day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hariansinggalang.co.id/penumpang-pesawat-dari-malaysia-dilaporkan-meninggal-di-rsup-m-djamil/|title=Penumpang Pesawat dari Malaysia Dilaporkan Meninggal di RSUP M Djamil|date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Responses==\n=== Central government ===\n[[File:Treatment Facilities List.jpg|thumb|Treatment Facilities List<ref name=\"Nasir\">{{Cite web|url=https://infeksiemerging.kemkes.go.id/situasi-infeksi-emerging/info-corona-virus/menteri-kesehatan-tetapkan-132-rumah-sakit-rujukan-covid-19/|title=Menteri Kesehatan Tetapkan 132 Rumah Sakit Rujukan COVID-19 \u00bb Info Infeksi Emerging Kementerian Kesehatan RI|last=Nasir|first=Post Author: Muchtar|date=2020-03-11|website=Info Infeksi Emerging Kementerian Kesehatan RI|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>|alt=]]\nIndonesia banned all flights from and to [[Mainland China]] starting from 5 February. The government also stopped giving [[Visa policy of Indonesia|free visa and visa on arrival]] for Chinese nationals. Those who live or have stayed in Mainland China in the previous 14 days have been barred from entering or transiting through Indonesia. Indonesians are discouraged from travelling to China.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-china-health-indonesia/indonesia-bars-entry-to-visitors-from-china-amid-evacuation-protest-idUKKBN1ZW09K\n|title=Indonesia bars entry to visitors from China amid evacuation protest\n|last1=Da Costa\n|first1=Agustinus Beo\n|last2=Suroyo\n|first2=Gayatri\n|last3=Davies\n|first3=Ed\n|last4=Cushing\n|first4=Christopher\n|last5=Kerry\n|first5=Frances\n|agency=Reuters\n|date=2 February 2020\n|accessdate=2 February 2020\n|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200216114517/https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-china-health-indonesia/indonesia-bars-entry-to-visitors-from-china-amid-evacuation-protest-idUKKBN1ZW09K\n|archive-date=16 February 2020\n|url-status=live\n}}</ref>\n\nStarting on 8 March, travel restrictions expanded to include [[Daejeon]] and [[Gyeongsangbuk-do]] in [[South Korea]], [[Lombardy]], [[Veneto]] and [[Emilia-Romagna]] regions of [[Italy]], and [[Tehran]] and [[Qom]] in [[Iran]] Visitors with travel history within these countries but outside the aforementioned regions have to provide a valid health certificate during check in for all transportation into Indonesia.<ref>{{Cite web\n|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/05/covid-19-indonesia-issues-travel-ban-for-hardest-hit-iran-south-korea-italy.html\n|title=COVID-19: Indonesia bars people from hardest-hit regions in Iran, South Korea, Italy\n|last=Post\n|first=The Jakarta\n|website=The Jakarta Post\n|language=en\n|access-date=2020-03-07\n}}</ref> Despite the restriction on travellers from [[South Korea]], Indonesia is still allowing flights from South Korea.<ref>{{Cite web\n|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/06/covid-19-indonesia-still-allows-flights-to-and-from-south-korea-amid-travel-ban.html\n|title=COVID-19: Indonesia still allows flights to and from South Korea amid travel ban\n|last=Post\n|first=The Jakarta\n|website=The Jakarta Post\n|language=en\n|access-date=2020-03-07\n}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Ministry of Health (Indonesia)|Ministry of Health]] ordered the installation of thermal scanners for at least 135 [[airport]] gates and port docks,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-03/02/c_138835417.htm|title=2 Indonesians found infected with COVID-19 domestically|author=Shi Yinglun|date=2020-03-02|work=Xinhua|accessdate=2020-03-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsflare.com/video/335034/health-education/indonesian-border-authorities-implement-thermal-scanners-at-airports-due-to-coronavirus-outbreak|title=Indonesian border authorities implement thermal scanners at airports due to coronavirus outbreak|date=2020-01-22|work=Newsflare|accessdate=2020-03-05}}</ref> and announced that provisioning over 100 hospitals with isolation rooms (to WHO-recommended standards) would begin.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-03-02/indonesia-records-first-cases-of-covid-19-coronavirus/12018090|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 has now reached Indonesia, President Joko Widodo confirms|author=Alan Weedon|date=2020-03-02|work=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=2020-03-05}}</ref> Starting on 4 March, [[Jakarta MRT]] also began scanning the temperature of passengers entering the stations and denying access to those with symptoms of high fever.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/1315360/coronavirus-update-mrt-begins-checking-passengers-temperature|title=Coronavirus Update; MRT Begins Checking Passengers' Temperature|last=Bhwana|first=Petir Garda|date=2020-03-04|website=Tempo|language=en|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref> After the first victim died, the Indonesian government admitted that they have difficulties in detect incoming imported cases on airports, doing contact tracing and also location history for each case.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/12/08091431/kasus-covid-19-terus-bertambah-sulitnya-deteksi-di-bandara-dan-tracing|title=Kasus Covid-19 Terus Bertambah: Sulitnya Deteksi di Bandara dan Tracing Kontak|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\nThe Indonesian government plans to turn a site on [[Galang Island]], [[Galang Refugee Camp|previously used as a]] [[refugee camp]] for [[Vietnamese boat people|Vietnamese asylum seekers]] into a 1,000-bed medical facility specially equipped to handle the coronavirus outbreak and other infectious diseases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/04/former-vietnamese-refugee-camp-near-batam-to-be-transformed-into-hospital-for-covid-19-patients.html|title=Indonesia to turn former Vietnamese refugee camp into hospital for COVID-19 patients|author=Fadli|date=2020-03-04|work=The Jakarta Post|accessdate=2020-03-05}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, the government designated 132 treatment facilities across Indonesia.<ref name=\"Nasir\"/> On 18 March, 227 additional hospitals (109 [[Indonesian National Armed Forces|military]] hospitals, 53 [[Indonesian National Police|police]] Hospitals and 65 [[State-owned enterprises of Indonesia|state-owned enterprises]] hospitals) are provisioned to cover more patients across the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4943816/pemerintah-tambah-rs-untuk-perawatan-pasien-virus-corona-totalnya-359|title=Pemerintah Tambah RS untuk Perawatan Pasien Virus Corona, Totalnya 359|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> The government also established [[Coronavirus Disease Mitigation Acceleration Task Force]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/13/indonesia-scrambles-to-contain-coronavirus-as-most-hospitals-not-ready.html|title=Indonesia scrambles to contain coronavirus as most hospitals not ready|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> [[:id:Doni Monardo|Doni Monardo]] has been appointed to lead this team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200313212424-4-144838/jokowi-tunjuk-doni-monardo-jadi-panglima-pemberantas-corona|title=Jokowi Tunjuk Doni Monardo Jadi Panglima Pemberantas Corona|last=dob|website=news|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> On the same day, Minister of Home Affairs Tito Karnavian urged all of Indonesian regional leaders to suspend all non-essential travel to foreign country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939923/cegah-tertular-corona-mendagri-minta-kepala-daerah-hingga-dprd-tak-ke-ln|title=Cegah Tertular Corona, Mendagri Minta Kepala Daerah hingga DPRD Tak ke LN|last=Prasetia|first=Andhika|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 March, the government of Indonesia declared the coronavirus outbreak in Indonesia as a national disaster.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kemenkes: Corona Bencana Nasional, Bukan Darurat Nasional|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939175/kemenkes-corona-bencana-nasional-bukan-darurat-nasional|publisher=Detik|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, Joko Widodo has called on all Indonesians to practice what epidemiologists call [[social distancing]] to slow the spread of COVID-19 in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/15/jokowi-calls-for-social-distancing-to-stem-virus-spread.html|title=Jokowi calls for 'social distancing' to stem virus spread|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> Indonesian tax authorities announced that they will move back the tax reporting deadline to 30 April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beritadaerah.co.id/2020/03/17/pelaporan-spt-tahunan-wajib-pajak-op-mundur-ke-30-april/|title=Pelaporan SPT Tahunan Wajib Pajak OP Mundur ke 30 April|last=Caratri|first=Endah|date=2020-03-17|website=Berita Daerah|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, the [[Ministry of State Owned Enterprises (Indonesia)|Ministry of State-Owned Enterprises]] instructed its employees ages 50 and above to work from home.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4939348/pegawai-kementerian-bumn-usia-50-tahun-kerja-dari-rumah-mulai-senin|title=Pegawai Kementerian BUMN Usia 50 Tahun Kerja dari Rumah Mulai Senin|last=Chandra|first=Ardan Adhi|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> President Joko Widodo also clarified that the decision to implement lockdown on cities or regencies are only to be made after consultation with the central government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beritadaerah.co.id/2020/03/16/jokowi-kurangi-mobilitas-untuk-cegah-penularan-covid-19-bukan-lockdown/|title=Jokowi, Kurangi Mobilitas untuk Cegah Penularan COVID-19, Bukan Lockdown|last=Trimahanani|first=Emy|date=2020-03-16|website=Berita Daerah|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> On the same day, as schools are closing in some regions, Minister of Education [[Nadiem Makarim]] announced readiness of the Ministry of Education to assist schools in online learning by providing free teaching platforms.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vibizmedia.com/2020/03/16/platform-gratis-bagi-siswa-belajar-di-rumah-kerjasama-dengan-mendikbud/|title=Platform Gratis Bagi Siswa Belajar di Rumah, Kerjasama Dengan Mendikbud|last=Nugrahani|first=Hanny|date=2020-03-16|website=Vibizmedia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> Minister of Finance Sri Mulyani announced a shifting of infrastructure budget of 1 trillion IDR into healthcare and pandemic prevention.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.beritadaerah.co.id/2020/03/17/demi-penyelamatan-rakyat-menkeu-siapkan-rp-1-triliun-tangani-penyebaran-coronak-kesehatan/|title=Demi Penyelamatan Rakyat, Menkeu Siapkan Rp 1 Triliun Tangani Penyebaran Corona|last=Trimahanani|first=Emy|date=2020-03-17|website=Berita Daerah|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n[[File:Athlete's village for Asian Games 2018, 2017.jpg|thumb|Former Asian Games athletes village turned into COVID-19 hospital|279x279px]]\nOn 17 March, COVID-19 health protocols have been released to public.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kompas.com/tren/read/2020/03/17/105258465/berikut-protokol-kesehatan-jika-alami-gejala-virus-corona|title=Berikut Protokol Kesehatan jika Alami Gejala Virus Corona|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sehatnegeriku.kemkes.go.id/baca/rilis-media/20200316/4033408/lakukan-protokol-kesehatan-jika-mengalami-gejala-covid-19/|title=Lakukan Protokol Kesehatan ini jika Mengalami Gejala Covid-19|date=2020-03-16|website=Sehat Negeriku|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Indonesia)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] also expanded the travel restriction to temporary abolish visa free entry to Indonesia for one month and deny transit or arrival for visitors who have been in [[Iran]], [[Italy]], [[Vatican City]], [[Spain]], [[France]], [[Germany]], [[Switzerland]], and [[United Kingdom]] within the past 14 days.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4942940/cegah-persebaran-corona-travelers-dari-8-negara-ini-dilarang-masuk-ri|title=Cegah Persebaran Corona, Travelers dari 8 Negara Ini Dilarang Masuk RI|last=Prasetia|first=Andhika|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, the government launching [https://www.covid19.go.id/ covid19.go.id] site, an official source of accurate information on controlling the spread of coronavirus in Indonesia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.antaranews.com/news/144002/govt-launches-official-website-furnishing-information-on-covid-19|title=Govt launches official website furnishing information on COVID-19|last=antaranews.com|website=Antara News|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4943936/informasi-tentang-corona-satu-pintu-pemerintah-luncurkan-situs-covid-19|title=Informasi tentang Corona Satu Pintu, Pemerintah Luncurkan Situs COVID-19|last=detikcom|first=Tim|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> On the same day, The Ministry of Finance also announced that [[Kemayoran Athletes Village]], a former athlete's housing for the [[2018 Asian Games]] will be converted to house COVID-19 patients who show only mild symptoms after consultation from doctors .<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/properti/d-4944169/wisma-atlet-kemayoran-jadi-tempat-isolasi-pasien-corona|title=Wisma Atlet Kemayoran Jadi Tempat Isolasi Pasien Corona|last=Kusuma|first=Hendra|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/ekonomi/20200318163126-92-484626/melihat-kapasitas-wisma-atlet-lokasi-isolasi-pasien-corona|title=Melihat Kapasitas Wisma Atlet, Lokasi Isolasi Pasien Corona|website=ekonomi|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/18/19194761/wisma-atlet-untuk-pasien-covid-19-wapres-ada-1800-tempat-tidur|title=Wisma Atlet untuk Pasien Covid-19, Wapres: Ada 1.800 Tempat Tidur|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref> The conversion was officially completed on 23 March <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/multimedia/2020/03/22/former-asian-games-athletes-village-turned-into-covid-19-hospital.html|title=Video: Former Asian Games athletes village turned into COVID-19 hospital|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, Bank of Indonesia decided to slash the bank rate to 4.5%, in addition to 6 other fiscal policies, in the attempt to shore up the economy amidst the COVID-19 crisis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vibiznews.com/2020/03/19/bi-memangkas-bi-7-drrr-ke-450-rilis-7-langkah-kebijakan-memitigasi-risiko-covid-19/|title=BI Memangkas BI 7-DRRR ke 4,50%, Rilis 7 Langkah Kebijakan; Memitigasi Risiko COVID-19|last=Pakasi|first=Alfred|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, the government is mulling over a plan to ban this year's Idul Fitri ''mudik'' (exodus) to prevent city dwellers from spreading the coronavirus to towns and villages across the archipelago.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/26/indonesia-may-ban-idul-fitri-exodus-to-stop-covid-19-transmission.html|title=Indonesia may ban Idul Fitri exodus to stop COVID-19 transmission|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, Jokowi refuses to impose lockdown on Jakarta. Bus routes connecting Jakarta and other cities and provinces will remain open following the cancellation of a plan to temporarily suspend operations of Greater Jakarta-based intercity and interprovincial (AKAP) buses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/30/jokowi-refuses-to-impose-lockdown-on-jakarta.html|title=Jokowi refuses to impose lockdown on Jakarta|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/30/buses-still-able-to-leave-and-enter-jakarta-despite-calls-for-quarantine.html|title=Buses still able to leave and enter Jakarta despite calls for quarantine|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> \n\nOn 31 March, Indonesia announces Rp 405 trillion COVID-19 budget, anticipates a 5% deficit in a historic move. The government will allocate Rp 75 trillion for healthcare spending, Rp 110 trillion for social protection and Rp 70.1 trillion for tax incentives and credit for enterprises. The biggest chunk, Rp 150 trillion, will be set aside for economic recovery programs including credit restructuring and financing for small and medium businesses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/indonesia-announces-rp-405-trillion-covid-19-budget-anticipates-5-deficit-in-historic-move.html|title=Indonesia announces Rp 405 trillion COVID-19 budget, anticipates 5% deficit in historic move|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n=== Regional government ===\n==== State of Emergency ====\n\n*'''Jakarta''': 20 March - 19 April<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/market/20200321130447-17-146650/ini-daftar-pemda-yang-sudah-tetapkan-darurat-corona|title=Ini Daftar Pemda yang Sudah Tetapkan Darurat Corona|last=Umah|first=Anisatul|website=market|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref name=\":19A\">{{Cite web|url=https://megapolitan.kompas.com/read/2020/03/28/17121551/pemprov-dki-perpanjang-masa-tanggap-darurat-covid-19-sampai-19-april-2020|title= Pemprov DKI Perpanjang Masa Tanggap Darurat Covid-19 sampai 19 April 2020|last=Mantalean|first=Vitorio|website=Kompas.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*'''Depok''': 18 March - 29 May<ref name=\":3\" />\n*'''Yogyakarta''': 20 March - 29 May<ref name=\":3\" />\n*'''Bogor''': Undisclosed<ref name=\":3\" />\n*'''East Java''': Undisclosed<ref name=\":3\" />\n*'''Banten''': Undisclosed<ref name=\":3\" />\n*'''East Kalimantan''': Undisclosed<ref name=\":3\" />\n*'''West Kalimantan''': Undisclosed<ref name=\":3\" />\n*'''West Java''': 19 March - 29 May<ref name=\":3\" />\n*'''Papua''': 17 March - 31 March<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/id-id/berita/unik/papua-siaga-darurat-corona/vp-BB11p6Pw|title=Papua Siaga Darurat Corona|website=www.msn.com|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n*'''Aceh''': 20 March - 29 May<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://humas.acehprov.go.id/plt-gubernur-aceh-tetapkan-status-tanggap-darurat-skala-provinsi-covid-19|title=Plt. Gubernur Aceh Tetapkan Status Tanggap Darurat Skala Provinsi COVID-19|website=humas.acehprov.go.id|date=26 March 2020|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n*'''North Sumatera''': 31 March - 29 May<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sumsel.antaranews.com/berita/452850/status-sumut-naik-menjadi-tanggap-darurat-covid-19|title=Status Sumut naik menjadi Tanggap Darurat COVID -19|last=Home|last2=Terkini|website=Antara News Sumsel|access-date=2020-03-31|last3=News|first3=Top|last4=Terpopuler|last5=Nusantara|last6=Nasional|last7=Palembang|first7=Berita|last8=Sumsel|first8=Info|last9=Daerah|first9=Lintas}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Regional Quarantine\n!No\n!Region\n!Date\n!Notes\n|-\n|1\n|Papua\n|26 March to 8 April 2020<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://health.detik.com/berita-detikhealth/d-4958790/heboh-rencana-karantina-wilayah-6-daerah-ini-sudah-duluan-memulainya|title=Heboh Rencana Karantina Wilayah, 6 Daerah Ini Sudah Duluan Memulainya|last=Mahardhika|first=Anjar|website=detikHealth|language=id|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|2\n|Tegal\n|30 March<ref name=\":8\" />\n|\n|-\n|3\n|Tasikmalaya\n|31 March <ref name=\":8\" />\n|\n|-\n|4\n|Bali\n|\n|\n|-\n|5\n|Solo\n|\n|\n|-\n|6\n|Maluku\n|\n|\n|}\n\n==== Aceh ====\nOn 12 March, acting Aceh governor Nova Iriansyah advised Acehnese to stay away from vices and activities that are incompatible with religious and Islamic sharia values.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939739/cegah-corona-pemprov-aceh-imbau-tak-cipika-cipiki-hingga-jauhi-maksiat|title=Cegah Corona, Pemprov Aceh Imbau Tak Cipika-cipiki hingga Jauhi Maksiat|last=Setyadi|first=Agus|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, due to the rapid rise of the number of coronavirus infections in the country, the province of [[Aceh]] decided to close schools until further notice.<ref>{{cite web|title=Antisipasi Corona, Mulai Senin Besok Sekolah di Aceh Libur, Siswa Bisa Belajar di Rumah|url=https://aceh.tribunnews.com/2020/03/15/antisipasi-corona-mulai-senin-besok-sekolah-di-aceh-libur-siswa-bisa-belajar-di-rumah|publisher=Tribun News|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, the city of Sabang started to implement travel restrictions to forbid foreign visitors from travelling to their city.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4941063/sabang-aceh-tolak-turis-asing-untuk-cegah-penyebaran-corona|title=Sabang Aceh Tolak Turis Asing untuk Cegah Penyebaran Corona|last=Setyadi|first=Agus|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, Nova Iriansyah declared a \"province-scale\" state of emergency in Aceh for 71 days, lasting until 29 May.<ref name=\":6\" />\n\n==== Banten ====\nOn 15 March, Governor of [[Banten]] [[Wahidin Halim]] declares \"extraordinary event\" and decides to close all schools for 2 weeks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939529/banten-klb-virus-corona-gubernur-liburkan-siswa-sekolah|title=Banten KLB Virus Corona, Gubernur Liburkan Siswa Sekolah|last=Rifa'i|first=Bahtiar|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n==== Central Java ====\nOn 13 March, the city of [[Surakarta|Solo]] in Central Java decided to close all primary schools (SD) and junior high school's (SMP) for next 2 weeks, after three positive cases are found in the city.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://regional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/13/23264941/solo-klb-corona-sd-dan-smp-diliburkan-14-hari|title=Solo KLB Corona, SD dan SMP Diliburkan 14 Hari|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> The mayor of Solo [[F. X. Hadi Rudyatmo]] has also declared that the area is under \"extraordinary event\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200313230652-20-483326/solo-deklarasikan-klb-corona|title=Solo Deklarasikan KLB Corona|website=nasional|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> On the same day, the [[Sragen Regency|Regency of Sragen]] decided to close all schools from kindergarten to junior high school throughout the regency for at least a week, while closure of senior high school in the regency would be decided by the provincial government.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pemkab Sragen Liburkan Sekolah|url=https://semarang.bisnis.com/read/20200314/535/1213253/pemkab-sragen-liburkan-sekolah|publisher=Bisnis|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 March, Central Java governor [[Ganjar Pranowo]] decided to close all kindergarten to junior high schools at the province. High schools would remain open during the examination season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita-jawa-tengah/d-4939462/corona-mewabah-gubernur-ganjar-liburkan-sekolah-se-jateng|title=Corona Mewabah, Gubernur Ganjar Liburkan Sekolah se-Jateng|last=Purbaya|first=Angling Adhitya|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> The [[Salatiga|city of Salatiga]] followed the same decision on 15 March. The city government would also provide a total of Rp. 3 billion for medical support.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sekolah Libur 2 Minggu, Salatiga Anggarkan Rp 3 Miliar Tangani Corona|url=https://regional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/15/08071641/sekolah-libur-2-minggu-salatiga-anggarkan-rp-3-miliar-tangani-corona|publisher=Kompas|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, the governor announced that schools under control of the provincial government will postpone their opening until 13 April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://joglosemarnews.com/2020/03/pemprov-jateng-resmi-perpanjang-libur-semua-sekolah-sampai-13-april-2020-kadisdikbud-sebut-demi-selamatkan-anak-karena-puncak-wabah-corona-diprediksi-terjadi-bulan-april/|title=Pemprov Jateng Resmi Perpanjang Libur Sekolah Sampai 13 April 2020. Kadisdikbud Sebut Demi Selamatkan Anak Karena Puncak Wabah Corona Diprediksi Terjadi Bulan April! \u00bb JOGLOSEMAR NEWS|last=Media|first=Joglosemar News|date=2020-03-25|website=JOGLOSEMAR NEWS|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, the city of Solo,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://regional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/26/08532971/klb-virus-corona-solo-diperpanjang-sampai-13-april-razia-siswa-yang|title=KLB Virus Corona Solo Diperpanjang sampai 13 April, Razia Siswa yang Berkeliaran Digiatkan|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> Semarang,<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rmoljateng.com/read/2020/03/26/26171/Semarang-Dan-Sukoharjo-Tetapkan-Masa-Libur-Sekolah-Diperpanjang-|title=Semarang Dan Sukoharjo Tetapkan Masa \"Libur\" Sekolah Diperpanjang|last=RMOL|website=rmoljateng.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> Salatiga,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jateng.sindonews.com/read/23299/1/pemkot-salatiga-perpanjang-pembelajaran-daring-hingga-13-april-2020-1585217032|title=Pemkot Salatiga Perpanjang Pembelajaran Daring hingga 13 April 2020|website=SINDOnews.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> and Sukoharjo Regency<ref name=\":7\" /> announced that kindergarten, primary, and junior high school's opening will be postponed until 13 April.\n\nOn 27 March, despite statements from President Jokowi that lockdowns are the authority of the central government, mayor of Tegal Dedy Yon Supriyono announced that Tegal will be on lockdown. He ordered that 49 road access to the city to be barricaded with movable concrete barriers, and visitors from outside will be thoroughly checked and have to undergone a 14-day quarantine period.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200327083557-20-487375/tegal-lockdown-49-jalan-akan-ditutup-beton-tamu-diisolasi|title=Tegal Lockdown: 49 Jalan Akan Ditutup Beton, Tamu Diisolasi|website=nasional|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> On the other hand, the Governor of Central Java Ganjar Pranowo insisted that the blockade will only happen at some part of the city of Tegal, not on the whole city.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200326211845-20-487320/ganjar-bantah-kota-tegal-local-lockdown-hanya-alun-alun-saja|title=Ganjar Bantah Kota Tegal Local Lockdown: Hanya Alun-alun Saja|website=nasional|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\n==== DKI Jakarta ====\n[[File:Location of reported COVID-19 cases in Jakarta as of 2 April 2020.jpg|alt=|thumb|Location of reported COVID-19 cases in Jakarta as of 2 April 2020 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://corona.jakarta.go.id/id|title=Jakarta Tanggap COVID-19|website=Jakarta Tanggap COVID-19|language=id|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>]]\nOn 2 March, in response to the confirmed cases, DKI Jakarta governor [[Anies Baswedan]] halted the issuance of permits for large gatherings.<ref>{{cite news |first=Arief |last=Ikhsanudin |title=Ada Positif Corona, Anies Tak Keluarkan Izin Keramaian Baru |url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4922558/ada-positif-corona-anies-tak-keluarkan-izin-keramaian-baru |accessdate=2 March 2020 |work=Detik.com|date=2 March 2020 |language=id}}</ref> These including concerts by [[Foals (band)|Foals]], [[Babymetal]], Head in the Clouds, and [[Dream Theater]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://megapolitan.kompas.com/read/2020/03/03/18531711/dampak-virus-corona-pemprov-dki-tangguhkan-izin-3-konser-ini|title=Dampak Virus Corona, Pemprov DKI Tangguhkan Izin 3 Konser Ini|last=Sari|first=Nursita|date=3 March 2020|website=Kompas.com|language=id|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303142152/https://megapolitan.kompas.com/read/2020/03/03/18531711/dampak-virus-corona-pemprov-dki-tangguhkan-izin-3-konser-ini|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kompas.com/hype/read/2020/03/14/135551166/virus-corona-jadi-pandemi-konser-dream-theater-di-indonesia-ditunda|title=Virus Corona Jadi Pandemi, Konser Dream Theater di Indonesia Ditunda|last=Aditia|first=Andika|date=14 March 2020|website=Kompas.com|language=id|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314145918/https://www.kompas.com/hype/read/2020/03/14/135551166/virus-corona-jadi-pandemi-konser-dream-theater-di-indonesia-ditunda|archive-date=14 March 2020|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, after 69 positive COVID-19 cases, several tourist destinations in Jakarta including  [[Ancol Dreamland]], multiple government-managed museums,  [[Ragunan Zoo]] and [[National Monument (Indonesia)|Monas]] was closed for 2 weeks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4938105/anies-tutup-monas-ragunan-hingga-ancol-2-pekan-untuk-cegah-corona|title=Anies Tutup Monas, Ragunan hingga Ancol 2 Pekan untuk Cegah Corona|last=Ikhsanudin|first=Arief|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://megapolitan.kompas.com/read/2020/03/13/18294191/pemprov-dki-tutup-ancol-ragunan-hingga-monas-selama-dua-pekan|title=Pemprov DKI Tutup Ancol, Ragunan hingga Monas Selama Dua Pekan|last=Sari |date=2020-03-13|first= Nursita|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://travel.detik.com/travel-news/d-4938356/bukan-hanya-monas-ancol-anies-juga-tutup-15-tempat-wisata-lain|title=Bukan Hanya Monas-Ancol, Anies Juga Tutup 15 Tempat Wisata Lain|last=Diah|first=Femi|website=detikTravel|language=id|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref> The Islamic organization [[Muhammadiyah]] formed a \"command centre\" allocating 20 hospitals in the country to handle the outbreak, with the centre being led by emergency medicine specialist [[Corona Rintawan]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Doctor called Corona helps Indonesia battle coronavirus |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/regional/2020/03/11/doctor-called-corona-helps-indonesia-battle-coronavirus |accessdate=13 March 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 March, Jakarta governor Anies Baswedan decided to suspend all school activities and examinations for two weeks in response to prevent further spread of the virus in the capital city of Jakarta.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/14/covid-19-jakarta-suspends-schools-exams-for-two-weeks.html|title=COVID-19: Jakarta suspends schools, exams for two weeks|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, Jakarta provincial government prepared 500 to 1,000 beds for [[Patient Under Investigation|patient under investigation (PUI)]] that will be placed on designated COVID-19 treatment facilities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4940014/pemprov-dki-siapkan-500-1000-tempat-tidur-di-rs-rujukan-untuk-pdp-corona|title=Pemprov DKI Siapkan 500-1.000 Tempat Tidur di RS Rujukan untuk PDP Corona|last=Azzahra|first=Tiara Aliya|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, [[Jakarta MRT|MRT Jakarta]], LRT and [[TransJakarta|Transjakarta]] started to reduce number of trips, [[List of TransJakarta corridors|corridors]] and timetables (06.00 - 18.00), however, this policy was retracted due to long queue in many bus stops and train stations in morning.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200315190337-4-145011/anies-pangkas-rute-jam-operasi-tj-mrt-dan-lrt-jakarta|title=Anies Pangkas Rute & Jam Operasi TJ, MRT, dan LRT Jakarta|last=Iqbal|first=Muhammad|website=news|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200315193139-4-145014/transjakarta-hanya-operasi-13-rute-mulai-besok-ini-daftarnya|title=TransJakarta Hanya Operasi 13 Rute Mulai Besok, Ini Daftarnya|last=Iqbal|first=Muhammad|website=news|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4941613/anies-armada-bus-transjakarta-mrt-disesuaikan-seperti-semula-di-rush-hour|title=Anies: Armada Bus Transjakarta-MRT Disesuaikan Seperti Semula di Rush Hour|last=Ikhsanudin|first=Arief|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> Odd-even policy will be halted during outbreak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20200315202118-4-145016/mulai-besok-anies-cabut-aturan-ganjil-genap-di-seluruh-dki|title=Mulai Besok, Anies Cabut Aturan Ganjil-Genap di Seluruh DKI|last=Iqbal|first=Muhammad|website=news|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, Anies Baswedan declared a state of emergency in Jakarta for the next 14 days, lasting until 2 April.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn 28 March, Jakarta provincial government extends the state of emergency until 19 April.<ref name=\":19A\"/>\n\nOn 2 April, Anies Baswedan Allocates Rp3tn to Fight Coronavirus Outbreak, the budget will be used to fund the city's fight against the virus up until May this year, by gradually allocating Rp1.3 trillion and an additional Rp2 trillion<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/1327240/anies-baswedan-allocates-rp3tn-to-fight-coronavirus-outbreak|title=Anies Baswedan Allocates Rp3tn to Fight Coronavirus Outbreak|last=Afifa|first=Laila|date=2020-04-02|website=Tempo|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==== East Java ====\n[[File:COVID-19 location in East Java (2 April 2020).png|thumb|Location of confirmed and suspected [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] cases in [[East Java]] (2 April 2020). ]]\nOn 15 March, the city of [[Malang]] announced that they will close all schools for two weeks. The closure will begin on 16 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kompas.id/baca/nusantara/2020/03/15/antisipasi-covid-19-sekolah-di-kota-malang-diliburkan/|title=Antisipasi Covid-19, Sekolah di Kota Malang Diliburkan|date=2020-03-15|website=Kompas.id|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\nOn the same day, the Governor of East Java [[Khofifah Indar Parawansa]] ordered the closure of all schools throughout the province. Educational institutions were advised to cancel any kind of student exchange until indefinite time, however national examination in the province would not be postponed.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gubernur Khofifah Putuskan Sekolah se-Jawa Timur Libur, UN Tetap Jalan|date=15 March 2020|url=https://surabaya.liputan6.com/read/4202688/gubernur-khofifah-putuskan-sekolah-se-jawa-timur-libur-un-tetap-jalan|publisher=Liputan6|accessdate=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, mayor of Malang Sutiaji decided to close all access to the city (lockdown), starting on 18 March. As of 16 March, there is no positive COVID-19 in Malang or in the province of East Java.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.merdeka.com/peristiwa/cegah-corona-wali-kota-tutup-akses-keluar-dan-masuk-kota-malang-mulai-lusa.html|title=Cegah Corona, Wali Kota Tutup Akses Keluar dan Masuk Kota Malang Mulai Lusa|website=merdeka.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref> He would later clarified that the lockdown only applies to the government of Malang, not the general populace.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://regional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/16/17050681/wali-kota-tidak-ada-penutupan-akses-menuju-kota-malang|title=Wali Kota: Tidak Ada Penutupan Akses Menuju Kota Malang|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, Khofifah declared a state of emergency for East Java.<ref name=\"9Positive\" />\n\n==== North Sumatera ====\n\nOn 31 March, the provincial government of North Sumatera declared a state of emergency until 29 May 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200331001556-20-488484/sumut-naikkan-status-penanganan-virus-corona|title=Sumut Naikkan Status Penanganan Virus Corona|website=nasional|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n==== Papua ====\nOn 24 March, the provincial government of Papua decided to close any in and out access to Papua except for logistics and medical workers starting from 26 March for 14 days.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Damarjati |first1=Danu |title=Darurat Corona, Akses Keluar-Masuk Papua Ditutup! |url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4951923/darurat-corona-akses-keluar-masuk-papua-ditutup |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=detikNews |date=24 March 2020 |language=id}}</ref> Indonesian Minister of Home Affairs [[Tito Karnavian]] disagreed with the decision, saying that the central government's advice to the regional governments is not to close transportation, but to ban mass gatherings.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Aji |first1=M Rosseno |title=Mendagri Tito Karnavian Tak Setuju Papua Tutup Akses |url=https://nasional.tempo.co/read/1323649/mendagri-tito-karnavian-tak-setuju-papua-tutup-akses/full&view=ok |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=Tempo.co |date=25 March 2020 |language=id}}</ref>\n\n==== South Sumatera ====\n\nOn 30 March, Jakabaring Athletes Village, a former athlete's housing for the [[2018 Asian Games]] in Palembang, be appointed by the Governor of South Sumatera [[Herman Deru]] to be the house of PUM's treatment (''ODP Center''). He named it as \"COVID-19 Healthy House\" (''Rumah Sehat COVID-19'').<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sumsel.tribunnews.com/2020/03/30/gubernur-sumsel-herman-deru-resmikan-rumah-sehat-di-jakabaring|title=Gubernur Sumsel, Herman Deru Resmikan Rumah Sehat di Jakabaring|website=Tribun Sumsel|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n==== West Java ====\nOn 14 March, the city of [[Depok]] and [[Bogor]] decided to close all schools from kindergarten to senior high school until 28 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://megapolitan.kompas.com/read/2020/03/14/18345331/pemkot-depok-liburkan-sekolah-dua-pekan-cegah-penyebaran-covid-19|title=Pemkot Depok Liburkan Sekolah Dua Pekan Cegah Penyebaran Covid-19|last=Mantalean|first=Vitorio |website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-14|date=2020-03-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://megapolitan.okezone.com/read/2020/03/14/338/2183466/antisipasi-korona-sd-hingga-smp-di-kota-bogor-diliburkan-2-pekan|title=Antisipasi Korona, SD hingga SMP di Kota Bogor Diliburkan 2 Pekan : Okezone Megapolitan|first=Putra Ramadhani|last= Astyawan|date=2020-03-14|work=okezone.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> This decision was also followed by the city of Bandung, in which the city opted to close schools for the next two weeks and advised schools to hold online teachings.<ref>{{cite web|author=Putra, Wisma|title=Pandemi Corona, Sekolah di Kota Bandung Libur Dua Pekan|url=https://news.detik.com/berita-jawa-barat/d-4939542/pandemi-corona-sekolah-di-kota-bandung-libur-dua-pekan|publisher=Detik|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, [https://pikobar.jabarprov.go.id/#/ West Java COVID-19 distribution map] has been released to public.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4940371/ridwan-kamil-ungkap-peta-persebaran-corona-di-jabar|title=Ridwan Kamil Ungkap Peta Persebaran Corona di Jabar|last=Putri|first=Zunita|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> The Regency of [[Bogor Regency|Bogor]] implement \"semi-lockdown\" on tourist area Puncak for foreign visitors, to prevent them from entering the area.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liputan6.com/news/read/4202960/cegah-corona-bupati-bogor-berlakukan-semi-lockdown-di-kawasan-puncak|title=Cegah Corona, Bupati Bogor Berlakukan Semi Lockdown di Kawasan Puncak|last=Liputan6.com|date=2020-03-16|website=liputan6.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>[[Jalak Harupat Stadium|Jalak Harupat]], [[Pakansari Stadium|Pakansari]] and [[Patriot Stadium (Indonesia)|Patriot Chandrabragha]] stadiums are being prepared for COVID-19 Mass Rapid Test.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/foto-news/d-4949014/stadion-patriot-kota-bekasi-jadi-lokasi-rapid-test|title=Stadion Patriot Kota Bekasi jadi Lokasi Rapid Test|last=Hermansyah|first=ANTARA FOTO/ Fakhri|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n\n==== West Kalimantan ====\nOn 15 March, the [[Governor of West Kalimantan|governor]] decided to impose quarantine for all students from kindergarten to senior high school level in the province, until a date which is yet to be decided. During the quarantine period, students must stay at their homes for studying. Exception is given for final year senior/vocational high school students on their respective national final examinations date.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cegah Penyebaran Corona, Gubernur Liburkan Seluruh Sekolah di Kalbar|url=http://kumparan.com/hipontianak/cegah-penyebaran-corona-gubernur-liburkan-seluruh-sekolah-di-kalbar-1t1wBFOxCXZ|publisher=Kumparan|accessdate=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Others ===\n====Universities====\nIn response of the outbreak, multiple universities opted to cancel classes and instead would teach students online.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nOn 16 March, at least 17 universities across Indonesia confirmed that conventional face-to-face lectures would be cancelled and would be replaced by online classes. Graduations and gatherings were cancelled and students and lecturers who had gone abroad from countries with confirmed coronavirus cases with any reasons should self-isolate at home. As of 14 March, numerous universities have closed their classes, such as [[University of Indonesia|Universitas Indonesia]] (UI),<ref>{{cite web|title=Dosen UI Pulang dari Negara Terdampak Corona Wajib Isolasi|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200303083000-20-479980/dosen-ui-pulang-dari-negara-terdampak-corona-wajib-isolasi|publisher=CNN Indonesia}}</ref> [[Gadjah Mada University|Universitas Gajah Mada]] (UGM), [[Bandung Institute of Technology|Institut Teknologi Bandung]] (ITB), [[:id:Universitas Gunadarma|Universitas Gunadharma]], [[Multimedia Nusantara University|Universitas Multimedia Nusantara]] (UMN), [[Indonesian State College of Accountancy|Sekolah Tinggi Akuntansi Negara]] (STAN), [[:id:Kalbis Institute|Kalbis Institut]], [[Bina Nusantara University|Binus University]], [[Atma Jaya Catholic University of Indonesia|Universitas Atmajaya]], [[:id:STIKOM The London School of Public Relations|London School Public Relations]] (LSPR), [[YARSI University|Universitas Yarsi]], [[Pelita Harapan University|Universitas Pelita Harapan]] (UPH), Telkom University, Universitas Atma Jaya Yogyakarta (UAJY),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita-jawa-tengah/d-4940365/corona-merebak-mahasiswa-uajy-kuliah-online-dan-tak-ada-kkn|title=Corona Merebak, Mahasiswa UAJY Kuliah Online dan Tak Ada KKN|last=Retaduari|first=Elza Astari|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> Universitas Hasanuddin (UNHAS),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939944/cegah-corona-unhas-terapkan-kuliah-online-dan-tunda-wisuda|title=Cegah Corona, Unhas Terapkan Kuliah Online dan Tunda Wisuda|last=Abdurrahman|first=Muhammad Nur|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> [[Tarumanagara University|Universitas Tarumanegara]] (UNTAR), [[IPB University|Insitut Pertanian Bogor]] (IPB),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4939505/cegah-penyebaran-corona-ipb-terapkan-kuliah-online-pulangkan-mahasiswa|title=Cegah Penyebaran Corona, IPB Terapkan Kuliah Online-Pulangkan Mahasiswa|last=Alfons|first=Matius|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> and [[:id:Universitas Al Azhar Indonesia|Universitas Al-Azhar Indonesia]] (UAI).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.medcom.id/pendidikan/news-pendidikan/ZkeBWZAK-15-kampus-terapkan-kuliah-online-untuk-cegah-korona|title=15 Kampus Terapkan Kuliah Online untuk Cegah Korona|date=14 March 2020|publisher=Medcom|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Makdori, Yopi|title=15 Perguruan Tinggi Gelar Kuliah Jarak Jauh, Ini Daftarnya|date=14 March 2020|url=https://www.liputan6.com/news/read/4201718/15-perguruan-tinggi-gelar-kuliah-jarak-jauh-ini-daftarnya|publisher=Liputan6|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref>[[University of Brawijaya]], a university in [[Malang]], creates a disinfection chamber as an effort to contain the coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/21/malang-university-students-invent-disinfection-chamber-to-prevent-covid-19-spread.html |title = Malang university students invent disinfection chamber to prevent COVID-19 spread}}</ref>\n\n==== Corporations ====\n[[File:Mandatory temperature checks warning sign in healthcare centers 01.jpg|thumb|Mandatory temperature checks warning in healthcare centres in Indonesia due to COVID-19 outbreaks in the country. (March 2020)|215x215px]]\nOn 14 March, [[Tokopedia]] and [[Gojek]] have begun trial for work at home operations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4939067/tokopedia-mulai-uji-coba-kerja-dari-rumah|title=Tokopedia Mulai Uji Coba Kerja dari Rumah|last=Rachman|first=Fadhly Fauzi|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bisnis.tempo.co/read/1319473/antisipasi-corona-gojek-uji-coba-karyawan-kerja-dari-rumah|title=Antisipasi Corona, Gojek Uji Coba Karyawan Kerja dari Rumah|last=Setiawan|first=Kodrat|date=2020-03-14|website=Tempo|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, [[Unilever Indonesia]] announced work-from-home policy for their office site, this policy will be started on 16 March until further notice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4939098/cegah-penyebaran-corona-unilever-ikut-terapkan-kerja-dari-rumah|title=Cegah Penyebaran Corona, Unilever Ikut Terapkan Kerja dari Rumah|last=Rachman|first=Fadhly Fauzi|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, [[Telkomsel]], [[Bank Mandiri]], [[Indonesian Financial Transaction Reports and Analysis Center|Indonesian Financial Transaction Reports and Analysis Centre]] and [[Bank Indonesia]] announced work-from-home and split-team policy, these policies will be started on 17 March until further notice.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/market/20200316170050-17-145263/karyawan-mandiri-telkomsel-bisa-kerja-di-rumah-mulai-besok|title=Karyawan Mandiri & Telkomsel Bisa Kerja di Rumah Mulai Besok|last=Wareza|first=Monica|website=market|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/moneter/d-4941817/pegawai-bi-bergiliran-kerja-dari-rumah|title=Pegawai BI Bergiliran Kerja dari Rumah|last=Laucereno|first=Sylke Febrina|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4942186/ppatk-terapkan-kerja-dari-rumah-tetap-awasi-pencucian-uang|title=PPATK Terapkan Kerja dari Rumah, Tetap Awasi Pencucian Uang?|last=Lidyana|first=Vadhia|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, [[Indonesia AirAsia|Indonesia Air Asia]] (QZ) suspend all domestic and international flights to overcome spread of pandemic. All domestic flights suspended between 1 April and 21 April 2020 while international flights between 1 April and 17 May 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://travel.detik.com/travel-news/d-4956479/airasia-setop-sementara-semua-penerbangan-indonesia|title=AirAsia Setop Sementara Semua Penerbangan Indonesia|last=Bonauli|website=detikTravel|language=id|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n[[Mayapada Group]] founder, [[Dato Sri Tahir]] donated Rp. 52b in form of Personal protective equipment, medical drugs, disinfectant, operational vehicles and also accommodation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4956124/sumbang-rp-52-m-untuk-lawan-corona-ini-pesan-orang-terkaya-ri|title=Sumbang Rp 52 M untuk Lawan Corona, Ini Pesan Orang Terkaya RI|last=Novika|first=Soraya|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March, [[Grab (company)|Grab]] donated US$10 Mio to reduce Covid-19 impact in Indonesia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inet.detik.com/cyberlife/d-4959842/grab-siapkan-rp-160-miliar-bantu-redam-dampak-corona-di-indonesia|title=Grab Siapkan Rp 160 Miliar Bantu Redam Dampak Corona di Indonesia|last=Ghivarianto|first=Reyhan Diandri|website=detikinet|language=id|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n==== Societal organizations ====\nOn 16 March, [[Indonesian Council of Ulama]] (MUI) and [[Muhammadiyah]] urge to substitute [[Friday prayer]] with [[Zuhr prayer]] and not to attend any religious activities within heavily virus-plagued areas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/16/19125761/fatwa-mui-umat-di-area-rawan-covid-19-boleh-tinggalkan-salat-jumat-diganti|title=Fatwa MUI: Umat di Area Rawan Covid-19 Boleh Tinggalkan Salat Jumat, Diganti Salat Zuhur|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://republika.co.id/share/q7812j428|title=Muhammadiyah: Bila Darurat, Shalat Berjamaah di Rumah|date=2020-03-15|website=Republika Online|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 March, [[Muhammadiyah]] advises Muslims to not perform [[tarawih]] in [[Ramadan]] and Idul Fitri prayers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/covid-19-muhammadiyah-advises-muslims-to-not-perform-tarawih-idul-fitri-prayers.html|title=COVID-19: Muhammadiyah advises Muslims to not perform \u2018tarawih\u2019, Idul Fitri prayers|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n=== Travel restrictions ===\nIndonesia has imposed denial of transit and visit for visitors who were in the following countries within the past 14 days:<ref name=\"travelrestriction\">{{cite web |title=Additional Measures of The Indonesian Government in Relation to Covid-19 Response |url=https://kemlu.go.id/portal/en/read/1135/siaran_pers/additional-measures-of-the-indonesian-government-in-relation-to-covid-19-response |website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Indonesia |publisher=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Indonesia |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n* February\n**{{Flag|China}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/02/02/17474161/antisipasi-corona-pendatang-dari-china-dilarang-masuk-ke-indonesia|title=Antisipasi Corona, Pendatang dari China Dilarang Masuk ke Indonesia|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-20}}</ref>\n*March\n**{{Flag|South Korea}}: [[Daegu]] and [[North Gyeongsang]] province<ref name=\"travelrestriction2\">{{cite web |title=Indonesian Government Policy on the Development of Covid - 19 Outbreak |url=https://kemlu.go.id/portal/en/read/1104/berita/indonesian-government-policy-on-the-development-of-covid-19-outbreak |website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Indonesia |publisher=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Indonesia |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n**{{Flag|Iran}}\n**{{Flag|Italy}}\n**{{Flag|Vatican City}}\n**{{Flag|Spain}}\n**{{Flag|France}}\n**{{Flag|Germany}}\n**{{Flag|Switzerland}}\n**{{Flag|United Kingdom}}\n**All Countries (2 April)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/indonesia-to-bar-foreigners-from-entering-in-bid-to-curb-imported-cases.html|title=Indonesia to bar foreigners from entering in bid to curb imported cases|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/31/20472021/imigrasi-larang-wna-masuk-ke-indonesia-mulai-2-april|title=Imigrasi Larang WNA Masuk ke Indonesia Mulai 2 April|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\nIn addition, Indonesia suspends visa free entry for all visitors into the country for one month. Visitors who wish to enter Indonesia must apply for a visa at the nearest embassy or consulate and produce a valid health certificate and state of purpose.\n\nIndonesians who return from the aforementioned countries are also subject to additional health screening and a 14-day stay-at-home notice or quarantine depending on appearing symptoms.\n\nOn 31 March, Indonesia will bar foreign nationals from transiting through or entering the country as the government steps up efforts to curb the spread of COVID-19 in the country without heeding growing calls for a complete lockdown to contain the pandemic. This policy start from 2 April until further notice, but destroy everything.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/31/20472021/imigrasi-larang-wna-masuk-ke-indonesia-mulai-2-april|title=Imigrasi Larang WNA Masuk ke Indonesia Mulai 2 April|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/31/indonesia-to-bar-foreigners-from-entering-in-bid-to-curb-imported-cases.html|title=Indonesia to bar foreigners from entering in bid to curb imported cases|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n==Criticism==\n\n=== Failure to detect the virus ===\nHealth experts are concerned that the country is failing to identify the transmission of the virus.<ref name=\"JakPost 20200229\">{{cite web\n|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/academia/2020/02/29/lets-not-kid-ourselves-indonesia-is-unlikely-to-be-covid-19-free-and-thats-not-our-biggest-problem.html\n|title=Let's not kid ourselves. Indonesia is unlikely to be COVID-19-free. And that's not our biggest problem.\n|author=Ary Hermawan\n|work=The Jakarta Post\n|date=29 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020\n}}</ref> Marc Lipsitch, professor of [[epidemiology]] at the [[Harvard T. H. Chan School of Public Health]], \"analysed air traffic out of the Chinese city at the centre of the outbreak in China and suggested in a report ... that Indonesia might have missed cases\" of [[coronavirus disease 2019]].<ref>{{cite news\n|first1=Karen\n|last1=McVeigh\n|first2=Emma\n|last2=Graham-Harrison\n|accessdate=2020-03-02\n|title=Academic stands by research querying Indonesia's claim to be coronavirus-free\n|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/14/indonesia-coronavirus-academic-harvard-marc-lipsitch\n|newspaper=The Guardian\n|date=14 February 2020\n|issn=0261-3077\n|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|accessdate=2020-03-02\n|title=Why are there no reported cases of coronavirus in Indonesia?\n|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/reported-cases-coronavirus-indonesia-200218112232304.html\n|website=aljazeera.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|author=Febriana Firdaus\n|accessdate=2020-03-02\n|title=Indonesian Screening May Be Missing Virus Carriers\n|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/02/19/indonesia-coronavirus-screening-may-miss-virus-carriers/\n}}</ref> Western diplomats<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.merdeka.com/dunia/kekhawatiran-as-dan-negara-barat-soal-penanganan-corona-di-indonesia.html\n|title=Kekhawatiran AS dan Negara Barat Soal Penanganan Corona di Indonesia\n|author=Wijaya Pandasurya\n|work=Merdeka.com\n|date=28 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020|language=id\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://nasional.kontan.co.id/news/kedutaan-besar-negara-barat-cemas-dengan-penanganan-virus-corona-di-Indonesia\n|title=Kedutaan besar negara Barat cemas dengan penanganan virus corona di Indonesia\n|editor=S.S. Kurniawan\n|work=Kontan\n|date=27 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020|language=id\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url= https://www.kompas.com/tren/read/2020/03/01/090000165/nol-kasus-perdana-menteri-australia-ragukan-penanganan-virus-corona-di\n|title= Nol Kasus, Perdana Menteri Australia Ragukan Penanganan Virus Corona di Indonesia\n|author=Nur Rohmi Aida\n|work=Kompas.com\n|date=1 March 2020\n|accessdate=2 March 2020|language=id\n}}</ref> as well as local<ref name=\"JakPost 20200229\"/><ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://jakartaglobe.id/news/we-dont-cover-things-up-indonesia-says-amid-doubts-over-its-covid19-handling\n|title=We Don't Cover Things Up, Indonesia Says Amid Doubts Over Its Covid-19 Handling\n|work=Jakarta Globe\n|date=28 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020\n}}</ref> and international<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/02/19/indonesia-coronavirus-screening-may-miss-virus-carriers/\n|title=Indonesian Screening May Be Missing Virus Carriers\n|author=Febriana Firdaus|work=Foreign Policy\n|date=19 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://time.com/5792180/southeast-asia-undetected-coronavirus/\n|title=A Silent Epidemic? Experts Fear the Coronavirus Is Spreading Undetected in Southeast Asia\n|last=Barron\n|first=Laignee\n|work=Time (magazine)\n|date=28 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/reported-cases-coronavirus-indonesia-200218112232304.html\n|title=Why are there no reported cases of coronavirus in Indonesia?\n|author1=Randy Mulyanto\n|author2=Febriana Firdaus\n|work=Al Jazeera\n|date=18 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020\n}}</ref> news outlets postulated that the lack of cases within Indonesia result from inadequate testing and under reporting, as opposed to sheer luck and [[Divine providence|divine intervention]].<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/health-environment/article/3051068/we-owe-it-god-indonesia-prays-how-it-keeping\n|title='We owe it to God': as Indonesia prays, how is it keeping the coronavirus at bay?\n|last=Cochrane\n|first=Joe\n|work=South China Morning Post\n|date=18 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-indonesia/indonesia-says-lack-of-coronavirus-cases-a-blessing-from-god-idUSKCN20L1DL\n|title=Indonesia says lack of COVID-19 cases a blessing from God\n|last=Da Costa\n|first=Agustinus Beo\n|work=Reuters\n|date=27 February 2020\n|accessdate=29 February 2020\n}}</ref> On March 22, a research suggested that the official number of infections may only reflect 2% of the real COVID-19 infections in Indonesia.<ref name=\"FirdausRatcliffe\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cmmid.github.io/topics/covid19/severity/global_cfr_estimates.html|title=Using a delay-adjusted case fatality ratio to estimate under-reporting|date=2020-03-22|website=CMMID Repository|language=en|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\n=== Budget for foreign social media influencers ===\nThe government faced backlash after instead pledging to set aside [[Rupiah|IDR]] 72 billion ($5m) to pay for social media influencers to attract tourists to Indonesia.<ref>{{cite news |title='Rp 72 Miliar Untuk Influencer': Cara Indonesia Merespon Virus Corona |trans-title='Rp 72 Billion for Influencers': How Indonesia Responds to the Coronavirus|url=https://www.tempo.co/abc/5348/rp-72-miliar-untuk-influencer-cara-indonesia-merespon-virus-corona |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Tempo |date=28 February 2020 |language=id}}</ref>\n\n=== Lack of transparency ===\nIndonesian president Joko Widodo is also criticized by Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://katadata.co.id/berita/2020/03/03/cegah-kepanikan-pengusaha-minta-pemerintah-jujur-soal-virus-corona|title=Cegah Kepanikan, Pengusaha Minta Pemerintah Jujur Soal Virus Corona - Katadata.co.id|date=2020-03-03|website=katadata.co.id|language=id|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> human rights groups,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.tempo.co/read/1319111/komnas-ham-minta-pemerintah-terbuka-soal-virus-corona|title=Komnas HAM Minta Pemerintah Terbuka Soal Virus Corona|last=Persada|first=Syailendra|date=2020-03-13|website=Tempo|language=en|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> and also by political party such as [[Golkar]] and [[Prosperous Justice Party|PKS]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20200313070528-20-483043/pks-minta-pemerintah-lebih-terbuka-soal-corona|title=PKS Minta Pemerintah Lebih Terbuka soal Corona|website=nasional|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4937624/daerah-sumber-corona-harus-diungkap-golkar-dorong-pemerintah-transparan|title=Daerah Sumber Corona Harus Diungkap, Golkar Dorong Pemerintah Transparan|last=Zhacky|first=Mochamad|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> for lack of transparency regarding the information of the COVID-19. Widodo have insisted not to share the travel history details of the patients that tested positive with coronavirus in an attempt to reduce panic and uneasiness in the general public.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/13/16163481/jokowi-akui-pemerintah-rahasiakan-sejumlah-informasi-soal-corona|title=Jokowi Akui Pemerintah Rahasiakan Sejumlah Informasi soal Corona|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-14}}</ref> The public had asked the government to release official national map of COVID-19 confirmed cases' location, as unofficial independent maps may provide incorrect data.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnnindonesia.com/teknologi/20200317193251-185-484321/pengamat-desak-peta-covid-19-nasional-mudah-dan-tak-mahal|title=Pengamat Desak Peta Covid-19 Nasional: Mudah dan Tak Mahal|website=CNN Indonesia|language=id|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Tests and treatment ===\nReports have surfaced about patients in Greater Jakarta having to wait for a long time to get tests or treatment for possible cases of the novel coronavirus disease (COVID-19) as referral hospitals face increasing strain.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/18/it-was-too-crowded-patients-find-it-hard-to-get-covid-19-tests-treatment.html|title='It was too crowded': Patients find it hard to get COVID-19 tests, treatment|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n\n=== Lockdown policies ===\nJoko Widodo has come under increased pressure to impose a partial lockdown on virus-plagued areas, with scientists saying the country is racing against time to curb the spread of COVID-19 before [[Lebaran|Eid al-Fitr]] and that a community quarantine could be the only solution to do exactly that.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/17/pressures-on-for-jokowi-to-close-cities.html|title=jokowi-to-close-cities|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> On 16 March, Jokowi stated that lockdown policies is the authority of the central government, and warned local government to not impose lockdown without the consent of central authority.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/03/16/15420291/jokowi-larang-pemerintah-daerah-lakukan-lockdown-terkait-covid-19|title=Jokowi Larang Pemerintah Daerah Lakukan Lockdown Terkait Covid-19|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, dozens of Indonesian medical professors have called for \u201clocal lockdowns\u201d, saying that the government's policy of physical distancing is not \u201ceffective\u201d. The government is drafting a regulation (PP) to stipulate the procedures and requirements for imposing regional quarantines.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/27/indonesia-to-issue-lockdown-regulation-as-covid-19-cases-continue-to-soar.html|title=Indonesia to issue lockdown regulation as COVID-19 cases continue to soar|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/27/top-indonesian-doctors-call-for-lockdown-say-physical-distancing-not-enough.html|title=Top Indonesian doctors call for lockdown, say physical distancing not enough|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==Impact==\n[[File:Panic buying in Jakarta due to COVID-19.jpg|thumb|Due to COVID-19, Jakartans rushes to panic-buy toilet rolls, food supplies, masks, hand sanitizers, etc.|183x183px]]\n\n=== Socioeconomic ===\n[[Surgical mask|Surgical face masks]] in Indonesia have soared in price by over six times the original retail value from around [[Rupiah|IDR]] 30,000 to IDR 185,000 (some sources stated it exceeds IDR 300,000) per box in some outlets after the announcement of two citizens test positive for the new coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |last1=newsflare |title=Surgical masks soar in price as Indonesia confirms first coronavirus cases |url=https://uk.news.yahoo.com/surgical-masks-soar-price-indonesia-100000524.html?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAANmOhqUlIngHeV1HFnkDnzqCebRJhM1sXAok9x_Lha-HNLAgrGcsrlm70ewYrq5HGMBGKJTOqFER4barcxpVoxPcHxINDGKvU_s9Xm_Y-ElsarCvFBmsVYKsLm7eAR5weSvrVnmrNIysLZ5inZV2XT7Dz4No52ssQsjP4IbPmmQl |accessdate=2 March 2020 |work=uk.news.yahoo.com |agency=Yahoo! news |publisher=Yahoo! news |date=2 March 2020}}</ref> [[Panic buying]] had been reported since mid-February before the first cases were confirmed.<ref>{{cite news |title=In 'virus-free' Indonesia, outbreak fears stoke panic buying frenzy |url=https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/health-environment/article/3050731/coronavirus-first-hong-kong-and-singapore-now-virus |accessdate=2 March 2020 |work=South China Morning Post |date=15 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref> President of Indonesia Joko Widodo has warned against hoarding of face masks and hand sanitizers<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jakartaglobe.id/news/jokowi-warns-against-hoarding-of-facemasks-amid-growing-coronavirus-fears|title=Jokowi Warns Against Hoarding of Facemasks Amid Growing Coronavirus Fears|website=Jakarta Globe|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref> and [[Indonesian National Police]] has started to crack down on suspected hoarders.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/04/police-seize-350-boxes-of-face-masks-during-raid-on-suspected-hoarder-in-west-jakarta.html|title=Police seize 350 boxes of face masks during raid on suspected hoarder in West Jakarta|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref>\n\n=== Economic ===\nFollowing the worldwide trend of stock price drops, the [[IDX Composite]] weakened even before the first confirmation of the disease in Indonesia.<ref>{{cite news \n|title=Indonesia stock index plunges to three-year low amid virus fears \n|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/02/27/indonesia-stock-index-plunges-to-three-year-low-amid-virus-fears.html \n|accessdate=2 March 2020 \n|work=The Jakarta Post \n|date=26 February 2020 \n|language=en\n}}</ref> In response to expected economic slowdown in Indonesia due to loss of Chinese economic activity, [[Bank Indonesia]] cut its interest rates by 25 basis points to 4.75% on 20 February.<ref>{{cite news \n|title=Bank Indonesia cuts rate, revises down growth target amid virus outbreak \n|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/02/20/bank-indonesia-cuts-rate-revises-down-growth-target-amid-virus-outbreak.html \n|accessdate=3 March 2020 \n|work=The Jakarta Post \n|date=20 February 2020 \n|language=en\n}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, as [[World Health Organization|WHO]] declares [[pandemic]], IDX Composite tumbled 4.2 percent to 4,937 when Thursday's session was opened, a level unseen in almost four years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/12/indonesian-stocks-slump-4-upon-opening-along-with-regional-markets-as-who-declares-pandemic.html|title=Indonesian stocks slump 4% upon opening along with regional markets as WHO declares pandemic|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, equity trading halted for first time since 2008 over pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/13/covid-19-indonesia-idx-trading-halted-first-time-2008.html|title=Trading halted for first time since 2008 over pandemic|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, Rupiah weakens to IDR 15,000 per dollar, touching a level unseen since October 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/17/rupiah-weakens-to-rp-15000-per-dollar-amid-stronger-greenback-covid-19-fears.html|title=Rupiah weakens to Rp 15,000 per dollar amid stronger greenback, COVID-19 fears|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vibiznews.com/2020/03/18/rupiah-rabu-ditutup-melemah-ke-rp15-218-usd-dollar-global-naik-sebagai-likuiditas-investor/|title=Rupiah Rabu Ditutup Melemah ke Rp15.218/USD; Dollar Global Naik sebagai Likuiditas Investor|last=Pakasi|first=Alfred|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-18}}</ref>[[File:JKSE Composite Index 2 weeks after case 1.jpg|thumb|220x220px|JKSE Composite Index 14 days after case #1 (2 March 2020)]]On 19 March, IDX Composite halted because of the sharp downturn of more than 5 percent. This is the fourth trading halt that IDX Composite experienced during the coronavirus crisis. Indonesia Financial Service Authority or OJK have mandated a suspension of trading if IDX Composite fell down more than 15 percent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vibiznews.com/2020/03/19/setelah-sempat-alami-trading-halt-ihsg-ditutup-anjlok-5-35-pada-sesi-pertama/|title=Setelah Sempat Alami Trading Halt, IHSG Ditutup Anjlok 5.35% Pada Sesi Pertama|last=Panjaitan|first=Selasti|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\nNumbers of shopping malls started to voluntarily close due to declining foot traffic; only pharmacies, groceries and ATM still operate with limited hours.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.detik.com/berita-ekonomi-bisnis/d-4952133/daftar-mal-tutup-sebagian-toko|title=Daftar Mal Tutup Sebagian Toko|last=Hamdani|first=Trio|website=detikfinance|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref>\n\n=== Tourism and leisure ===\nIndonesian tourism is also suffering the effect, with Bali suffering a 33% drop in tourism arrivals when compared to January, and a steep 96% reduction of Chinese travellers. [[Hotel]]s are taking on an exceptionally low occupancy rate, with some hotels experiencing 5% and even 0% occupancy rate due to overspecialization on Chinese visitors, increasing travel restrictions from source countries, and an overall fear of the virus.<ref>{{Cite web\n|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/03/05/despite-no-recorded-cases-bali-tourism-still-catches-cold-from-covid-19-outbreak.html\n|title=Despite no recorded cases, Bali tourism still catches cold from COVID-19 outbreak\n|website=The Jakarta Post\n|language=en\n|access-date=2020-03-07\n}}</ref> There is however an increase in interest for domestic tourism,<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2020/feb/20/balis-been-through-a-lot-holiday-islands-tourism-industry-hit-by-coronavirus-fears\n|title='Bali's been through a lot': holiday island's tourism industry hit by coronavirus fears \n|author=Krithika Varagur\n|work=The Guardian\n|date=2020-02-20\n|accessdate=2020-03-07\n|language=en\n}}</ref> and Chinese tourists already on the island have generally opted to extend their stay.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/se-asia/no-going-back-balis-chinese-tourists-fear-coronavirus-hit-homeland\n|title=No going back: Bali's Chinese tourists fear coronavirus-hit homeland\n|work=The Straits Times\n|date=2020-02-29\n|accessdate=2020-03-07\n|language=en\n}}</ref> All beaches in Bali are temporarily closed for public.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://travel.detik.com/fototravel/d-4960404/potret-penutupan-seluruh-pantai-di-kuta-bali|title=Potret Penutupan Seluruh Pantai di Kuta Bali|last=Istimewa|website=detikTravel|language=id|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>[[File:Pantai Puruih Padang Tacelak Era Wali Kota Mahyeldi.jpg|thumb|180x180px|left|A beach in [[Padang]] appear to be quiet as the Indonesian government calls on the public to implement [[social distancing]]]]\n\n[[Jakarta ePrix]] race of the [[2019\u201320 Formula E season]] will also be postponed due to coronavirus concerns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/1318147/jakarta-formula-e-race-postponed-due-to-coronavirus-concerns|title=Jakarta Formula E Race Postponed Due to Coronavirus Concerns|last=Bhwana|first=Petir Garda|date=2020-03-11|website=Tempo|language=en|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref> The city's Capital Investment and One-Stop Service (PM-PTSP) announced it plans to postpone any public events with mass-gatherings from March to April following the news of increasing number of COVID-19 cases to 27.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.tempo.co/read/1318081/jakarta-plans-to-stop-public-events-as-coronavirus-cases-climb|title=Jakarta Plans to Stop Public Events as Coronavirus Cases Climb|last=Bhwana|first=Petir Garda|date=2020-03-11|website=Tempo|language=en|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref>\n\nNumerous music events such has by Rich Brian, Hammersonic, Dream Theater, Babymetal, Slipknot, ONE OK ROCK, and electronic dance music festival \"We Are Connected\" has been suspended in the country because of the coronavirus concerns.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/lifestyle/20200314190622-33-144899/gara-gara-corona-konser-dream-theater-di-jakarta-ditunda|title=Gara-gara Corona, Konser Dream Theater di Jakarta Ditunda|last=dob|website=lifestyle|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/lifestyle/20200313133534-35-144667/hammersonic-festival-2020-batal-akan-ada-kembali-pada-2021|title=Hammersonic Festival 2020 Batal, akan Ada Kembali pada 2021|last=TV|first=CNBC Indonesia|website=lifestyle|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jabar.tribunnews.com/2020/03/12/akibat-virus-corona-10-dj-internasional-batal-tampil-di-we-are-connected-bali-april-ini|title=Akibat Virus Corona, 10 DJ Internasional Batal Tampil di We Are Connected Bali, April Ini|website=Tribun Jabar|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hot.liputan6.com/read/4193429/akibat-virus-corona-6-konser-ini-batal-digelar-di-indonesia|title=Akibat Virus Corona, 6 Konser Ini Batal Digelar di Indonesia|last=Liputan6.com|date=2020-03-04|website=liputan6.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://coconuts.co/jakarta/lifestyle/japanese-rock-band-one-ok-rock-postpones-jakarta-concert-amid-coronavirus-outbreak/|title=Japanese rock band ONE OK ROCK postpones Jakarta concert amid coronavirus outbreak|date=17 March 2020|website=Coconuts Jakarta|publisher=Coconuts Media Limited|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317122623/https://coconuts.co/jakarta/lifestyle/japanese-rock-band-one-ok-rock-postpones-jakarta-concert-amid-coronavirus-outbreak/|archive-date=17 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nSeveral local films, such as ''KKN di Desa Penari'', ''Tersanjung The Movie'', and ''Generasi 90-an: Melankolia'', has been delayed, also because of the novel coronavirus pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.merdeka.com/jatim/dampak-corona-film-kkn-desa-penari-ditunda-penayangannya-di-bioskop.html|title=Dampak Corona, Film KKN di Desa Penari Ditunda Penayangannya di Bioskop|website=merdeka.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fimela.com/news-entertainment/read/4206608/imbas-virus-corona-penayangan-film-tersanjung-the-movie-ditunda|title=Imbas Virus Corona, Penayangan Film Tersanjung The Movie Ditunda|last=Fimela.com|website=fimela.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://merahputih.com/post/read/rilis-generasi-90-an-melankolia-akhirnya-ditunda|title=Rilis Generasi 90-an: Melankolia Akhirnya Ditunda|last=Yani|first=Muchammad|date=2020-03-26|website=MerahPutih|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n[[Indonesia International Motor Show]] 2020 will be postponed due to the coronavirus crisis.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://otomotif.kompas.com/read/2020/03/17/071200415/iims-2020-ditunda-karena-corona-uang-peserta-pameran-dikembalikan-100|title=IIMS 2020 Ditunda karena Corona, Uang Peserta Pameran Dikembalikan 100 Persen|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=Kompas.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n[[Indonesian Wikipedia]] gathering (along with other Indonesian languages edition, such as [[Javanese Wikipedia]], [[Sundanese Wikipedia]], [[Minangkabau Wikipedia]], etc.) called \"[[:meta:WikiNusantara 2020|WikiNusantara]]\" (similar to [[Wikimania]] but on national scale) scheduled at the end of March is cancelled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://meta.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Konferensi_WMID_2020/Menu&diff=19897627&oldid=19630268|title=Difference between revisions of \"Template:Konferensi WMID 2020/Menu\" - Meta|website=meta.wikimedia.org}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n{{clear}}\n\n== Stimuli policy ==\n=== First stage ===\nTo reduce the impact of COVID-19 pandemic to the national economy, the Government of Indonesia releases a IDR 10.3 trilion stimulus policy to the tourism sector, in the form of ticket price discounts and restaurant tax deductions. \nThe IDR 10.3 trilion budget is given to provide discounted ticket prices for 10 tourist destinations, such as [[Batam]], [[Denpasar]], [[Yogyakarta]], [[Labuan Bajo]], [[Lombok]], [[Malang]], [[Manado]], [[Lake Toba]] ([[Silangit Airport]]), [[Tanjung Pandan]], and [[Tanjungpinang]], which applies from March to May 2020. Ticket prices for low-cost airlines are discounted by 50%, medium-service by 48%, and full-service by 45%.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://industri.kontan.co.id/news/pemerintah-tetapkan-insentif-penerbangan-tiket-pesawat-diskon-hingga-50|title=Pemerintah tetapkan insentif penerbangan, tiket pesawat diskon hingga 50%|last=|first=|date=2020-02-25|website=Kontan.co.id|language=id|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> Specifically for this ticket price discount, the stimulus fund comes from the IDR 444.39 billion-state budget (APBN) for a discounted value of 30% and 25% of passengers per flight.<ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/ekonomi/20200226091352-532-478192/jurus-jokowi-lawan-virus-corona-dengan-diskon-tiket-pesawat|title=Jurus Jokowi Lawan Virus Corona dengan Diskon Tiket Pesawat|last=Ananda|first=Aria|date=|website=CNNIndonesia.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> Additionally, there are additional ticket discounts paid by Angkasa Pura I and Angkasa Pura II in the amount of Rp100 billion and PT Pertamina (Persero) in the amount of Rp260 billion through avtur price discounts, so the total ticket price stimulus is IDR 960 billion so that the ticket price can be discounted by 50%.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wartaekonomi.co.id/read273843/lihat-nih-terbang-ke-10-destinasi-wisata-ini-diskonnya-hingga-50|title=Lihat Nih! Terbang ke 10 Destinasi Wisata Ini, Diskonnya hingga 50%|date=2020-02-26|website=Warta Ekonomi|language=id|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nThe stimulus in the form of restaurant taxes borne by the central government was also provided with a value of Rp3.3 trillion. Thus, there is no restaurant tax in the 10 tourist destinations above, but as compensation the local government will get a grant from the central government.<ref name=\":11\" />\n\n==Notable people==\n=== Confirmed cases ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Notable individuals confirmed COVID-19 positive\n!No\n!Name\n!Announcement Date\n!Status\n!Status Date\n!Note\n|-\n|1\n|dr Muhammad Budi Hidayat\n|13 March\n|Recovered<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita-jawa-timur/d-4954587/2-pasien-positif-corona-rsua-sembuh-termasuk-kepala-kkp-i-surabaya|title=2 Pasien Positif Corona RSUA Sembuh, Termasuk Kepala KKP I Surabaya|last=Azmi|first=Faiq|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://surabaya.kompas.com/read/2020/03/27/06400551/dua-pekan-dirawat-kepala-kkp-kelas-i-surabaya-sembuh-dari-covid-19|title=Dua Pekan Dirawat, Kepala KKP Kelas I Surabaya Sembuh dari Covid-19|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n|25 March 2020\n|Head of Class I Port Health Office of Surabaya\n|-\n|2\n|[[Budi Karya Sumadi]]\n|14 March\n|\n|\n|[[Indonesian Minister of Transportation|Minister of Transportation]]\n|-\n|3\n|{{ill|Andrea Dian|id}}\n|18 March<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hot.detik.com/celeb/d-4948770/andrea-dian-umumkan-positif-corona|title=Andrea Dian Umumkan Positif Corona|last=Febrian|first=Prih Prawesti|website=detikhot|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n|\n|\n|Actress\n|-\n|4\n|[[Bima Arya Sugiarto]]\n|19 March<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4946411/wali-kota-bogor-bima-arya-positif-corona|title=Wali Kota Bogor Bima Arya Positif Corona|last=Mawardi|first=Isal|website=Detik.com|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n|\n|\n|Mayor of [[Bogor]]\n|-\n|5\n|{{ill|Detri Warmanto|id}}\n|20 March<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hot.detik.com/celeb/d-4947822/pemain-film-3-srikandi-detri-warmanto-positif-corona|title=P