apar Virus Corona|last=Ramadhan|first=Dony Indra|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n|COVID-19 (+)\n|Deputy Chairperson, West Java regional representative council of [[Indonesian Democratic Party of Struggle|PDI-P]]\n|-\n|13\n|27 March 2020\n|27 March 2020\n|Kariadi General Hospital, Semarang, Central Java\n|{{ill|Imam Suroso|id}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4956120/pdp-corona-anggota-dpr-f-pdip-imam-suroso-meninggal-dunia|title=PDP Corona, Anggota DPR F-PDIP Imam Suroso Meninggal Dunia|last=Mawardi|first=Isal|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n|COVID-19 (+)\n|Member of Commission IX, [[People's Representative Council]]\n|-\n|14\n|27 March 2020\n|27 March 2020\n|RSUD Bogor\n|Yuniarto Budi Santosa, [[Dentist|drg.]], [[Master of Public Health|M.&nbsp;km.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bogor.pojoksatu.id/baca/kabid-kesehatan-kota-bogor-meninggal-positif-corona-diisolasi-di-rsud|title=Kabid Kesehatan Kota Bogor Meninggal Positif Corona, Diisolasi di RSUD|last=amin|first=ikrar|website=Berita dan Kabar Pilihan di Bogor - PojokBogor.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4956252/positif-corona-seorang-kabid-di-dinkes-kota-bogor-meninggal-dunia|title=Positif Corona, Seorang Kabid di Dinkes Kota Bogor Meninggal Dunia|last=Mawardi|first=Isal|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n|COVID-19 (+)\n|Head of Health Office, Bogor City\n|-\n|15\n|26 March 2020\n|27 March 2020\n|RSUD Kab Tangerang\n|Willy Dreeskandar<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oto.detik.com/berita/d-4956934/wartawan-otomotif-meninggal-sempat-tak-diurus-5-jam-di-rs-rujukan|title=Wartawan Otomotif Meninggal, Sempat Tak Diurus 5 Jam di RS Rujukan|last=Pratama|first=Rizki|website=detikoto|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gridoto.com/read/222078812/mengenang-willy-f-16-dreeskandar-wartawan-otomotif-yang-memiliki-banyak-nama-panggilan|title=Mengenang Willy F-16 Dreeskandar, Wartawan Otomotif yang Memiliki Banyak Nama Panggilan - Semua Halaman - GridOto.com|last=GridOto.com|website=www.gridoto.com|language=id|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n|COVID-19 (+)\n|Former automotive journalist\n|-\n|16\n|12 Maret 2020\n|31  March 2020\n|RSPI Sulianti Saroso\n|Ninuk Dwi Pusponingrum<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haibunda.com/trending/20200331160343-93-88077/curhat-perawat-rscm-sebelum-meninggal-karena-corona-rela-mati-demi-profesi|title=Curhat Perawat RSCM Sebelum Meninggal karena Corona, Rela Mati Demi Profesi|last=Hafadzoh|first=Siti|website=trending|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n|COVID-19 (+)\n|Nurse of Cipto Mangunkusumo General Hospital\n|-\n|17\n|30  March 2020\n|31  March 2020\n|Mohammad Hoesin General Hospital in Palembang, South Sumatra\n|H. Efrizal Syamsudin, dr., M.M.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4960492/idi-kembali-umumkan-dua-dokter-positif-corona-yang-meninggal-dunia|title=IDI Kembali Umumkan Dua Dokter Positif Corona yang Meninggal Dunia|last=Nufus|first=Wilda|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/04/01/two-hospital-directors-die-of-covid-19-as-indonesian-doctors-call-for-transparency.html|title=Two hospital directors die of COVID-19 as Indonesian doctors call for transparency|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n|COVID-19 (+)\n|RSUD Prabumulih Director\n|-\n|18\n|31  March 2020\n|31  March 2020\n|Pelni General Hospital, West Jakarta\n|Ratih Purwarini, dr.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita/d-4960492/idi-kembali-umumkan-dua-dokter-positif-corona-yang-meninggal-dunia|title=IDI Kembali Umumkan Dua Dokter Positif Corona yang Meninggal Dunia|last=Nufus|first=Wilda|website=detiknews|language=id-ID|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/04/01/two-hospital-directors-die-of-covid-19-as-indonesian-doctors-call-for-transparency.html|title=Two hospital directors die of COVID-19 as Indonesian doctors call for transparency|last=Post|first=The Jakarta|website=The Jakarta Post|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n|COVID-19 (+)\n|RS. Duta Indah Director\n|-\n|19\n|2 April 2020\n|2 April 2020\n|Mintoharjo Navy Hospital, Jakarta\n|Laksma TNI (Purn) dr Jeane P.M.R. Winaktu<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.tempo.co/read/1326919/1-lagi-dokter-meninggal-karena-corona-total-jadi-12-orang|title=1 Lagi Dokter Meninggal Karena Corona, Total Jadi 12 Orang|last=Persada|first=Syailendra|date=2020-04-02|website=Tempo|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nasional.kompas.com/read/2020/04/02/14024811/mantan-kepala-dinas-kesehatan-tni-al-tutup-usia|title=Mantan Kepala Dinas Kesehatan TNI AL Tutup Usia|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|website=KOMPAS.com|language=id|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|COVID-19 (+)\n|Former Chief of the Navy Health Service Dr. Mintohardjo\n|-\n|20\n|2 April 2020\n|2 April 2020\n|Mintoharjo Navy Hospital, Jakarta\n|Letkol (K)W Mulatsih<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hot.grid.id/read/182088387/tni-berduka-dokter-bedah-syaraf-wanita-pertama-di-indonesia-jadi-korban-keganasan-virus-corona-ini-kata-ikatan-dokter-indonesia|title=TNI Berduka, Dokter Bedah Syaraf Wanita Pertama di Indonesia Jadi Korban Keganasan Virus Corona, Ini Kata Ikatan Dokter Indonesia - Halaman 3 - Grid Hot|website=hot.grid.id|language=id|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|COVID-19 (+)\n|Head of the Cilandak Marine Hospital Nurse Department\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Indonesia| ]]\n", "name_user": "Othello95", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDefinition", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Indonesia"}
{"title_page": "I Funny", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Refimprove|date=August 2018}}\n{{Primary sources|date=February 2016}}}}\n{{Infobox book\n<!-- |italic title = (see above) -->\n| name             = I Funny: A Middle School Story\n| authors          = James Patterson and Chris Grabenstain\n| illustrator      = Laura Park\n| country          = United States\n| language         = English\n| series           = Upper school\n| genre            = Comedy, Mystery\n| publisher        = Little, Brown and Company\n| pub_date         = 2012\n| media_type       = Print (hardcover or paperback)\n| pages            =  305\n| followed_by      = I Even Funnier\n}} \n\n'''''I Funny: A Middle School Story''''', simply known as '''''I Funny''''', is a ''[[realistic fiction]]'' novel by ''[[James Patterson|Jack me hoff]]'' and ''[[Chris Grabenstein]]''. It was published by ''[[Little, Brown and Company]]'' in 2012. It is followed by ''I Even Funnier'' (2013), ''I Totally Funniest'' (2015), ''I Funny TV'' (2016), ''I Funny: School of Laughs'' (2017) and ''The Nerdiest, Wimpiest, Dorkiest I Funny Ever'' (2018).''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://toppsta.com/books/details/the-nerdiest-wimpiest-dorkiest-i-funny-ever-i-funny-6-1|title=THE NERDIEST, WIMPIEST, DORKIEST I FUNNY EVER: (I FUNNY 6)|author=James Patterson|website=Toppsta.com\\accessdate=17 August 2018}}</ref>''\n\n==Summary==\nThe broad humor that runs throughout this heavily illustrated story from Patterson and Grabenstein masks personal pain, demonstrating resiliency in the face of tragedy. Wheelchair-bound middle-schooler Jamie has recently moved in with his aunt\u2019s cheerless family, including\u2014a bit too conveniently\u2014school bully Stevie, Jamie\u2019s new \u201cadoptive brother.\u201d Despite Jamie\u2019s desire to be treated like an ordinary kid (one of the more important themes the authors emphasize) and a dark, lingering unknown (only late in the novel does Jamie reveal the reason for his paralysis and his parents\u2019 absence), humor abounds. Much of it derives from Jamie\u2019s comedic aspirations (he calls himself a \u201csit-down comic\u201d), which are fueled by his friends\u2019 reactions to his one-liners and the encouragement of his warmhearted uncle. Park\u2019s wisecracking cartoons (not all seen by PW) play an integral role in the storytelling, laying bare Jamie\u2019s fears, triumphs, and sense of humor. Not all the jokes land, but plenty do, and the value of having an author with as vast a reach as Patterson put a disabled character in the spotlight shouldn\u2019t be underestimated. Ages 8\u201312. Agent: Robert Barnett at Williams & Connolly. (Dec.)\n\n<br />\n\n==Characters==\n*'''Jamie Grimm''' is the [[disability|disabled]] [[protagonist]] of the story. He enters the Planet's Funniest Kid Comic Contest and wins the Long Island competition, then moves on to the state competition and wins. Next he will go to the Regionals in [[Boston]]. He was involved in a serious car accident two years prior that killed his parents and his younger sister, Jenny, and left him [[paralyzed]] from the legs down, and puts him in a [[wheelchair]]. He is later relocated from his home in [[Cornwall, New York|Cornwall]] in Upstate New York to his aunt and uncle's family (who he nicknamed \"the Smileys\" because they never smile, even when Jamie makes a joke) in [[Long Beach, New York|Long Beach]].\n* '''Suzie Orolvsky''' (AKA '''Cool Girl''') is a girl that Jamie carries her books for. They become good friends and she kisses Jamie at night in the light of the full moon. It is stated that Jamie and Gaynor both have feelings for her. She eventually had to move away to Chicago\n\n* '''Stevie Kosgrov''' is Jamie's adoptive brother and bully. He often makes jokes at his expense saying Jamie is successful because he is disabled.\n* '''Uncle Frankie''' is Jamie's other uncle. He owns Frankie's Good Eats by the Sea Diner and is shown to be very talented with yo-yo tricks.\n* '''Joey Gaynor''' is one of Jamie's best friends. He has long hair, a nose ring, and several tattoos. He is said to be obsessed with girls.\n* '''Jimmy Pierce''' is one of Jamie's best friends. He is said to be nerdy, has glasses, and wears this black hat with a flat top and broad rim. He is a total brainiac and knows everything.\n* '''Gilda Gold''' is Jamie's girlfriend and admirer.\n She is shown to be a [[Boston Red Sox]] fan. \n* '''Shecky''' is a kid from [[Schenectady]] who competes in the New York finals. He tells distasteful and usually insulting jokes, and is overconfident and arrogant. His catch phrase after telling a joke is \"Ba-Boom. Nailed it!\".\n* '''Judy Nazemetz''' is a girl from Manhattan who competes in the New York finals. She is Jamie's friend and apparently has a contract with [[Disney]] to become the next [[Hannah Montana]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n<!-- Adding external links to an article or user page for the purpose of promoting a website or a product is not allowed and is considered to be spam. Although the specific links may be allowed under some circumstances, ( e.g. Amazon, Internet Movie Database) repeatedly adding links will in most cases result in all of them being removed. -->\n* [http://www.middleschoolbooks.com/ Official James Patterson Middle School web site]\n* [http://www.JamesPatterson.com/ Official James Patterson US web site]\n* [https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14781201-i-funny Reviews]\n\n[[Category:Novels by James Patterson]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Refimprove|date=August 2018}}\n{{Primary sources|date=February 2016}}}}\n{{Infobox book\n<!-- |italic title = (see above) -->\n| name             = I Funny: A Middle School Story\n| authors          = James Patterson and Chris Grabenstain\n| illustrator      = Laura Park\n| country          = United States\n| language         = English\n| series           = Upper school\n| genre            = Comedy, Mystery\n| publisher        = Little, Brown and Company\n| pub_date         = 2012\n| media_type       = Print (hardcover or paperback)\n| pages            =  305\n| followed_by      = I Even Funnier\n}} \n\n'''''I Funny: A Middle School Story''''', simply known as '''''I Funny''''', is a ''[[realistic fiction]]'' novel by ''[[James Patterson]]'' and ''[[Chris Grabenstein]]''. It was published by ''[[Little, Brown and Company]]'' in 2012. It is followed by ''I Even Funnier'' (2013), ''I Totally Funniest'' (2015), ''I Funny TV'' (2016), ''I Funny: School of Laughs'' (2017) and ''The Nerdiest, Wimpiest, Dorkiest I Funny Ever'' (2018).''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://toppsta.com/books/details/the-nerdiest-wimpiest-dorkiest-i-funny-ever-i-funny-6-1|title=THE NERDIEST, WIMPIEST, DORKIEST I FUNNY EVER: (I FUNNY 6)|author=James Patterson|website=Toppsta.com\\accessdate=17 August 2018}}</ref>''\n\n==Summary==\nThe broad humor that runs throughout this heavily illustrated story from Patterson and Grabenstein masks personal pain, demonstrating resiliency in the face of tragedy. Wheelchair-bound middle-schooler Jamie has recently moved in with his aunt\u2019s cheerless family, including\u2014a bit too conveniently\u2014school bully Stevie, Jamie\u2019s new \u201cadoptive brother.\u201d Despite Jamie\u2019s desire to be treated like an ordinary kid (one of the more important themes the authors emphasize) and a dark, lingering unknown (only late in the novel does Jamie reveal the reason for his paralysis and his parents\u2019 absence), humor abounds. Much of it derives from Jamie\u2019s comedic aspirations (he calls himself a \u201csit-down comic\u201d), which are fueled by his friends\u2019 reactions to his one-liners and the encouragement of his warmhearted uncle. Park\u2019s wisecracking cartoons (not all seen by PW) play an integral role in the storytelling, laying bare Jamie\u2019s fears, triumphs, and sense of humor. Not all the jokes land, but plenty do, and the value of having an author with as vast a reach as Patterson put a disabled character in the spotlight shouldn\u2019t be underestimated. Ages 8\u201312. Agent: Robert Barnett at Williams & Connolly. (Dec.)\n\n<br />\n\n==Characters==\n*'''Jamie Grimm''' is the [[disability|disabled]] [[protagonist]] of the story. He enters the Planet's Funniest Kid Comic Contest and wins the Long Island competition, then moves on to the state competition and wins. Next he will go to the Regionals in [[Boston]]. He was involved in a serious car accident two years prior that killed his parents and his younger sister, Jenny, and left him [[paralyzed]] from the legs down, and puts him in a [[wheelchair]]. He is later relocated from his home in [[Cornwall, New York|Cornwall]] in Upstate New York to his aunt and uncle's family (who he nicknamed \"the Smileys\" because they never smile, even when Jamie makes a joke) in [[Long Beach, New York|Long Beach]].\n* '''Suzie Orolvsky''' (AKA '''Cool Girl''') is a girl that Jamie carries her books for. They become good friends and she kisses Jamie at night in the light of the full moon. It is stated that Jamie and Gaynor both have feelings for her. She eventually had to move away to Chicago\n\n* '''Stevie Kosgrov''' is Jamie's adoptive brother and bully. He often makes jokes at his expense saying Jamie is successful because he is disabled.\n* '''Uncle Frankie''' is Jamie's other uncle. He owns Frankie's Good Eats by the Sea Diner and is shown to be very talented with yo-yo tricks.\n* '''Joey Gaynor''' is one of Jamie's best friends. He has long hair, a nose ring, and several tattoos. He is said to be obsessed with girls.\n* '''Jimmy Pierce''' is one of Jamie's best friends. He is said to be nerdy, has glasses, and wears this black hat with a flat top and broad rim. He is a total brainiac and knows everything.\n* '''Gilda Gold''' is Jamie's girlfriend and admirer.\n She is shown to be a [[Boston Red Sox]] fan. \n* '''Shecky''' is a kid from [[Schenectady]] who competes in the New York finals. He tells distasteful and usually insulting jokes, and is overconfident and arrogant. His catch phrase after telling a joke is \"Ba-Boom. Nailed it!\".\n* '''Judy Nazemetz''' is a girl from Manhattan who competes in the New York finals. She is Jamie's friend and apparently has a contract with [[Disney]] to become the next [[Hannah Montana]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n<!-- Adding external links to an article or user page for the purpose of promoting a website or a product is not allowed and is considered to be spam. Although the specific links may be allowed under some circumstances, ( e.g. Amazon, Internet Movie Database) repeatedly adding links will in most cases result in all of them being removed. -->\n* [http://www.middleschoolbooks.com/ Official James Patterson Middle School web site]\n* [http://www.JamesPatterson.com/ Official James Patterson US web site]\n* [https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14781201-i-funny Reviews]\n\n[[Category:Novels by James Patterson]]\n", "name_user": "Margret43gloobershallent", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(The authors name was slightly adjusted to fit his new legally changed name)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/I_Funny"}
