{"title_page": "Shorea singkawang", "text_new": "{{taxobox\n|status = CR\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|regnum = [[Plantae]]\n|unranked_divisio = [[Angiosperms]]\n|unranked_classis = [[Eudicots]]\n|unranked_ordo = [[Rosids]]\n|ordo = [[Malvales]]\n|familia = [[Dipterocarpaceae]]\n|genus = ''[[Shorea]]''\n|species = '''''S. singkawang'''''\n|binomial = ''Shorea singkawang''\n|binomial_authority = (Miq.) Burck\n|}}\n\n'''''Shorea singkawang''''' (called, along with some other species in the genus ''[[Shorea]]'', '''dark red meranti''' or '''meranti merah''') is a species of [[plant]] in the family [[Dipterocarpaceae]]. It is found in [[Indonesia]], [[Malaysia]], and [[Thailand]]. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].\n\n==Sources==\n* Ashton, P. 1998.  [https://www.iucnredlist.org/details/33480/all ''Shorea singkawang''].   [https://web.archive.org/web/20140627094911/http://www.iucnredlist.org/ 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. ]  Downloaded on 23 August 2007.\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5490789}}\n\n[[Category:Shorea|singkawang]]\n[[Category:Trees of Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Trees of Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Trees of Thailand]]\n[[Category:Critically endangered flora of Asia]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n\n\n{{Dipterocarpaceae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{taxobox\n|status = CR\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|regnum = [[Plantae]]\n|unranked_divisio = [[Angiosperms]]\n|unranked_classis = [[Eudicots]]\n|unranked_ordo = [[Rosids]]\n|ordo = [[Malvales]]\n|familia = [[Dipterocarpaceae]]\n|genus = ''[[Shorea]]''\n|species = '''''S. singkawang'''''\n|binomial = ''Shorea singkawang''\n|binomial_authority = (Miq.) Burck\n|}}\n\n'''''Shorea singkawang''''' (called, along with some other species in the genus ''[[Shorea]]'', '''dark red meranti''' or '''Meranti Merah''') is a species of [[plant]] in the family [[Dipterocarpaceae]]. It is found in [[Indonesia]], [[Malaysia]], and [[Thailand]]. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].\n\n==Sources==\n* Ashton, P. 1998.  [htt